{"type":"USJ","version":"3.1","content":[{"type":"book","marker":"id","content":["English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"],"code":"2CH"},{"type":"para","marker":"ide","content":["UTF-8\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"h","content":["2 Chronicles \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc1","content":["The Second Book of Chronicles \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc2","content":["2 Chronicles \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc3","content":["2Ch \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt1","content":["The Second Book of Chronicles \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"1","sid":"2CH 1"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 1:1"},"Sulaiman the son of Dawood was firmly established in his kingdom, and the LORD\n",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:1 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["When rendered in ALL CAPITAL LETTERS, “LORD” or “ALLAH” is the translation of Allah’s Proper\nName."]}],"caller":"+"}," his Allah",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:1 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The Hebrew word rendered “Allah” is “אֱלֹהִ֑ים”\n(Elohim)."]}],"caller":"+"}," was with him, and made him exceedingly great. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 1:2"},"Sulaiman spoke to all Israel, to the captains of thousands and of hundreds, to the judges, and to every prince in all\nIsrael, the heads of the fathers’ households. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 1:3"},"So Sulaiman, and all the assembly with him, went to the high place that was at Gibeon; for Allah’s Tent of Meeting was\nthere, which the LORD’s servant Musa had made in the wilderness.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 1:4"},"But Dawood had brought Allah’s ark up from Kiriath Jearim to the place that Dawood had prepared for it; for he had pitched\na tent for it at Jerusalem. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 1:5"},"Moreover the bronze altar that Bezalel the son of Uri, the son of Hur, had made was there before the LORD’s tabernacle;\nand Sulaiman and the assembly were seeking counsel there. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 1:6"},"Sulaiman went up there to the bronze altar before the LORD, which was at the Tent of Meeting, and offered one thousand\nburnt offerings on it. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 1:7"},"That night, Allah appeared to Sulaiman and said to him, “Ask for what you want me to give you.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 1:8"},"Sulaiman said to Allah, “You have shown great loving kindness to Dawood my father, and have made me king in his place.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 1:9"},"Now, Allah the LORD, let your promise to Dawood my father be established; for you have made me king over a people like the\ndust of the earth in multitude. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 1:10"},"Now give me wisdom and knowledge, that I may go out and come in before this people; for who can judge this great people\nof yours?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 1:11"},"Allah said to Sulaiman, “Because this was in your heart, and you have not asked riches, wealth, honour, or the life of\nthose who hate you, nor yet have you asked for long life; but have asked for wisdom and knowledge for yourself, that you may\njudge my people, over whom I have made you king, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 1:12"},"therefore wisdom and knowledge is granted to you. I will give you riches, wealth, and honour, such as none of the kings\nhave had who have been before you had, and none after you will have.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 1:13"},"So Sulaiman came from the high place that was at Gibeon, from before the Tent of Meeting, to Jerusalem; and he reigned\nover Israel. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 1:14"},"Sulaiman gathered chariots and horsemen. He had one thousand and four hundred chariots and twelve thousand horsemen that\nhe placed in the chariot cities, and with the king at Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 1:15"},"The king made silver and gold to be as common as stones in Jerusalem, and he made cedars to be as common as the sycamore\ntrees that are in the lowland. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 1:16"},"The horses which Sulaiman had were brought out of Egypt and from Kue. The king’s merchants purchased them from Kue.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CH 1:17"},"They brought up and brought out of Egypt a chariot for six hundred pieces of silver, and a horse for one hundred and\nfifty.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The pieces of silver were probably shekels, so 600 pieces would be about 13.2 pounds or 6 kilograms of\nsilver, and 150 would be about 3.3 pounds or 1.5 kilograms of silver."]}],"caller":"+"}," They also exported them to the Hittite kings and the\nSyrian",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, Aramean"]}],"caller":"+"}," kings. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"2","sid":"2CH 2"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 2:1"},"Now Sulaiman decided to build a house for the LORD’s name, and a house for his kingdom.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 2:2"},"Sulaiman counted out seventy thousand men to bear burdens, eighty thousand men who were stone cutters in the mountains,\nand three thousand and six hundred to oversee them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 2:3"},"Sulaiman sent to Huram the king of Tyre, saying, “As you dealt with Dawood my father, and sent him cedars to build him a\nhouse in which to dwell, so deal with me. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 2:4"},"Behold,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:4 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["“Behold”, from “הִנֵּה”, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is often used\nas an interjection."]}],"caller":"+"}," I am about to build a house for the name of the LORD my Allah, to dedicate it to him, to burn before him\nincense of sweet spices, for the continual show bread, and for the burnt offerings morning and evening, on the Sabbaths, on the\nnew moons, and on the set feasts of the LORD our Allah. This is an ordinance forever to Israel.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 2:5"},"“The house which I am building will be great; for our Allah is greater than all gods.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 2:6"},"But who is able to build him a house, since heaven and the heaven of heavens can’t contain him? Who am I then, that I\nshould build him a house, except just to burn incense before him?\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 2:7"},"“Now therefore send me a man skilful to work in gold, in silver, in bronze, in iron, and in purple, crimson, and blue, and\nwho knows how to engrave engravings, to be with the skilful men who are with me in Judah and in Jerusalem, whom Dawood my\nfather provided. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 2:8"},"“Send me also cedar trees, cypress trees, and algum trees out of Lebanon; for I know that your servants know how to cut\ntimber in Lebanon. Behold, my servants will be with your servants,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 2:9"},"even to prepare me timber in abundance; for the house which I am about to build will be great and wonderful.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 2:10"},"Behold, I will give to your servants, the cutters who cut timber, twenty thousand\ncors",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:10 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["1 cor is the same as a homer, or about 55.9 U. S. gallons (liquid) or 211 litres or 6 bushels, so 20,000\ncors of wheat would weigh about 545 metric tonnes"]}],"caller":"+"}," of beaten wheat, twenty thousand\nbaths",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:10 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["1 bath is one tenth of a cor, or about 5.6 U. S. gallons or 21 litres or 2.4 pecks. 20,000 baths of\nbarley would weigh about 262 metric tonnes."]}],"caller":"+"}," of barley, twenty thousand baths of wine, and twenty thousand baths of oil.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 2:11"},"Then Huram the king of Tyre answered in writing, which he sent to Sulaiman, “Because the LORD loves his people, he has\nmade you king over them.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 2:12"},"Huram continued, “Blessed be the LORD, Allah of Israel, who made heaven and earth, who has given to Dawood the king a\nwise son, endowed with discretion and understanding, who would build a house for the LORD, and a house for his kingdom.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 2:13"},"Now I have sent a skilful man, endowed with understanding, of Huram my father’s,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 2:14"},"the son of a woman of the daughters of Dan; and his father was a man of Tyre, skilful to work in gold, in silver, in\nbronze, in iron, in stone, in timber, and in purple, in blue, in fine linen, and in crimson, also to engrave any kind of\nengraving and to devise any device; that there may be a place appointed to him with your skilful men, and with the skilful men\nof my lord Dawood your father. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 2:15"},"“Now therefore the wheat, the barley, the oil, and the wine, which my lord has spoken of, let him send to his servants;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 2:16"},"and we will cut wood out of Lebanon, as much as you need. We will bring it to you in rafts by sea to Joppa; then you\nshall carry it up to Jerusalem.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CH 2:17"},"Sulaiman counted all the foreigners who were in the land of Israel, after the census with which Dawood his father had\ncounted them; and they found one hundred and fifty-three thousand and six hundred.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CH 2:18"},"He set seventy thousand of them to bear burdens, eighty thousand who were stone cutters in the mountains, and three\nthousand and six hundred overseers to assign the people their work.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"3","sid":"2CH 3"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 3:1"},"Then Sulaiman began to build the LORD’s house at Jerusalem on Mount Moriah, where the LORD appeared to Dawood his father,\nwhich he prepared in the place that Dawood had appointed, on the threshing floor of Ornan the Jebusite.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 3:2"},"He began to build in the second day of the second month, in the fourth year of his reign.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 3:3"},"Now these are the foundations which Sulaiman laid for the building of Allah’s house. The length by\ncubits",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:3 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A cubit is the length from the tip of the middle finger to the elbow on a man’s arm, or about 18 inches\nor 46 centimetres."]}],"caller":"+"}," after the first measure was sixty cubits, and the width twenty cubits.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 3:4"},"The porch that was in front, its length, according to the width of the house, was twenty cubits, and the height one\nhundred and twenty; and he overlaid it within with pure gold. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 3:5"},"He made the larger room with a ceiling of cypress wood, which he overlaid with fine gold, and ornamented it with palm\ntrees and chains. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 3:6"},"He decorated the house with precious stones for beauty. The gold was gold from Parvaim.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 3:7"},"He also overlaid the house, the beams, the thresholds, its walls, and its doors with gold; and engraved cherubim on the\nwalls. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 3:8"},"He made the most holy place. Its length, according to the width of the house, was twenty cubits, and its width twenty\ncubits; and he overlaid it with fine gold, amounting to six hundred\ntalents.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:8 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A talent is about 30 kilograms or 66 pounds or 965 Troy ounces, so 600 talents is about 18 metric\ntonnes"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 3:9"},"The weight of the nails was fifty shekels",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:9 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A shekel is about 10 grams or about 0.32 Troy ounces, so 50\nshekels was about 0.5 kilograms or about 16 Troy ounces."]}],"caller":"+"}," of gold. He overlaid the upper rooms with gold.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 3:10"},"In the most holy place he made two cherubim by carving; and they overlaid them with gold.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 3:11"},"The wings of the cherubim were twenty cubits long: the wing of the one was five cubits, reaching to the wall of the\nhouse; and the other wing was five cubits, reaching to the wing of the other cherub.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 3:12"},"The wing of the other cherub was five cubits, reaching to the wall of the house; and the other wing was five cubits,\njoining to the wing of the other cherub. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 3:13"},"The wings of these cherubim spread themselves out twenty cubits. They stood on their feet, and their faces were towards\nthe house. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 3:14"},"He made the veil of blue, purple, crimson, and fine linen, and ornamented it with cherubim.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 3:15"},"Also he made before the house two pillars of thirty-five cubits height, and the capital that was on the top of each of\nthem was five cubits. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 3:16"},"He made chains in the inner sanctuary, and put them on the tops of the pillars; and he made one hundred pomegranates, and\nput them on the chains. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CH 3:17"},"He set up the pillars before the temple, one on the right hand, and the other on the left; and called the name of that on\nthe right hand Jachin, and the name of that on the left Boaz. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"4","sid":"2CH 4"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 4:1"},"Then he made an altar of bronze, twenty cubits",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:1\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A cubit is the length from the tip of the middle finger to the elbow on a man’s arm, or about 18 inches or 46\ncentimetres."]}],"caller":"+"}," long, twenty cubits wide, and ten cubits high. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 4:2"},"Also he made the molten sea",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:2 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, pool, or, reservoir"]}],"caller":"+"}," of ten cubits from brim to brim. It was round,\nfive cubits high, and thirty cubits in circumference. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 4:3"},"Under it was the likeness of oxen, which encircled it, for ten cubits, encircling the sea. The oxen were in two rows, cast\nwhen it was cast. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 4:4"},"It stood on twelve oxen, three looking towards the north, and three looking towards the west, and three looking towards\nthe south, and three looking towards the east; and the sea was set on them above, and all their hindquarters were inward.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 4:5"},"It was a handbreadth thick; and its brim was made like the brim of a cup, like the flower of a lily. It received and held\nthree thousand baths.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A bath is about 5.6 U. S. gallons or 21.1 litres, so 3,000 baths is about 16,800 gallons\nor 63.3 kilolitres."]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 4:6"},"He also made ten basins, and put five on the right hand, and five on the left, to wash in them. The things that belonged\nto the burnt offering were washed in them; but the sea was for the priests to wash in.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 4:7"},"He made the ten lamp stands of gold according to the ordinance concerning them; and he set them in the temple, five on the\nright hand, and five on the left. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 4:8"},"He made also ten tables, and placed them in the temple, five on the right side, and five on the left. He made one hundred\nbasins of gold. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 4:9"},"Furthermore he made the court of the priests, the great court, and doors for the court, and overlaid their doors with\nbronze. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 4:10"},"He set the sea on the right side of the house eastward, towards the south.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 4:11"},"Huram made the pots, the shovels, and the basins. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["So Huram finished doing the work that he did for king Sulaiman in Allah’s house:\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 4:12"},"the two pillars, the bowls, the two capitals which were on the top of the pillars, the two networks to cover the two\nbowls of the capitals that were on the top of the pillars, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 4:13"},"and the four hundred pomegranates for the two networks; two rows of pomegranates for each network, to cover the two bowls\nof the capitals that were on the pillars. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 4:14"},"He also made the bases, and he made the basins on the bases;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 4:15"},"one sea, and the twelve oxen under it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 4:16"},"Huram his father also made the pots, the shovels, the forks, and all its vessels for king Sulaiman, for the LORD’s house,\nof bright bronze. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CH 4:17"},"The king cast them in the plain of the Jordan, in the clay ground between Succoth and Zeredah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CH 4:18"},"Thus Sulaiman made all these vessels in great abundance; for the weight of the bronze could not be determined.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CH 4:19"},"Sulaiman made all the vessels that were in Allah’s house, the golden altar also, and the tables with the show bread on\nthem; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2CH 4:20"},"and the lamp stands with their lamps, to burn according to the ordinance before the inner sanctuary, of pure gold;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2CH 4:21"},"and the flowers, the lamps, and the tongs of gold that was perfect gold;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"2CH 4:22"},"and the snuffers, the basins, the spoons, and the fire pans of pure gold. As for the entry of the house, its inner doors\nfor the most holy place and the doors of the main hall of the temple were of gold.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"5","sid":"2CH 5"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 5:1"},"Thus all the work that Sulaiman did for the LORD’s house was finished. Sulaiman brought in the things that Dawood his\nfather had dedicated, even the silver, the gold, and all the vessels, and put them in the treasuries of Allah’s house.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 5:2"},"Then Sulaiman assembled the elders of Israel, and all the heads of the tribes, the princes of the fathers’ households of\nthe children of Israel, to Jerusalem, to bring up the ark of the LORD’s covenant out of Dawood’s city, which is Zion.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 5:3"},"So all the men of Israel assembled themselves to the king at the feast, which was in the seventh month.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 5:4"},"All the elders of Israel came. The Levites took up the ark;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 5:5"},"and they brought up the ark, the Tent of Meeting, and all the holy vessels that were in the Tent; these the Levitical\npriests brought up. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 5:6"},"King Sulaiman and all the congregation of Israel, who were assembled to him, were before the ark, sacrificing sheep and\ncattle that could not be counted or numbered for multitude. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 5:7"},"The priests brought in the ark of the LORD’s covenant to its place, into the inner sanctuary of the house, to the most\nholy place, even under the wings of the cherubim. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 5:8"},"For the cherubim spread out their wings over the place of the ark, and the cherubim covered the ark and its poles above.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 5:9"},"The poles were so long that the ends of the poles were seen from the ark in front of the inner sanctuary; but they were\nnot seen outside; and it is there to this day. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 5:10"},"There was nothing in the ark except the two tablets which Musa put at Horeb, when the LORD made a covenant with the\nchildren of Israel, when they came out of Egypt. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 5:11"},"When the priests had come out of the holy place (for all the priests who were present had sanctified themselves, and\ndidn’t keep their divisions; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 5:12"},"also the Levites who were the singers, all of them, even Asaph, Heman, Jeduthun, and their sons and their brothers,\narrayed in fine linen, with cymbals and stringed instruments and harps, stood at the east end of the altar, and with them one\nhundred and twenty priests sounding with trumpets); \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 5:13"},"when the trumpeters and singers were as one, to make one sound to be heard in praising and thanking the LORD; and when\nthey lifted up their voice with the trumpets and cymbals and instruments of music, and praised the LORD, saying,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“For he is good; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for his loving kindness endures forever!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"m","content":["then the house was filled with a cloud, even the LORD’s house,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 5:14"},"so that the priests could not stand to minister by reason of the cloud; for the LORD’s glory filled Allah’s house.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"6","sid":"2CH 6"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 6:1"},"Then Sulaiman said, “The LORD has said that he would dwell in the thick darkness.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 6:2"},"But I have built you a house and home, a place for you to dwell in forever.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 6:3"},"The king turned his face, and blessed all the assembly of Israel: and all the assembly of Israel stood.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 6:4"},"He said, “Blessed be the LORD, Allah of Israel, who spoke with his mouth to Dawood my father, and has with his hands\nfulfilled it, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 6:5"},"‘Since the day that I brought my people out of the land of Egypt, I chose no city out of all the tribes of Israel to build\na house in, that my name might be there and I chose no man to be prince over my people Israel;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 6:6"},"but now I have chosen Jerusalem, that my name might be there; and I have chosen Dawood to be over my people Israel.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 6:7"},"Now it was in the heart of Dawood my father to build a house for the name of the LORD, Allah of Israel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 6:8"},"But the LORD said to Dawood my father, ‘Whereas it was in your heart to build a house for my name, you did well that it\nwas in your heart; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 6:9"},"nevertheless you shall not build the house; but your son who will come out of your body, he shall build the house for my\nname.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 6:10"},"“The LORD has performed his word that he spoke; for I have risen up in the place of Dawood my father, and sit on the\nthrone of Israel, as the LORD promised, and have built the house for the name of the LORD, Allah of Israel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 6:11"},"There I have set the ark, in which is the LORD’s covenant, which he made with the children of Israel.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 6:12"},"He stood before the LORD’s altar in the presence of all the assembly of Israel, and spread out his hands\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 6:13"},"(for Sulaiman had made a bronze platform, five cubits",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A cubit is the length from the tip of the middle finger to the elbow on a man’s arm, or about 18 inches or 46\ncentimetres."]}],"caller":"+"}," long, and five cubits wide, and three cubits high, and had set it in the middle of the court; and he stood on\nit, and knelt down on his knees before all the assembly of Israel, and spread out his hands towards heaven)\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 6:14"},"and he said, “LORD, Allah of Israel, there is no Allah like you in heaven or on earth; you who keep covenant and loving\nkindness with your servants who walk before you with all their heart;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 6:15"},"who have kept with your servant Dawood my father that which you promised him. Yes, you spoke with your mouth, and have\nfulfilled it with your hand, as it is today. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 6:16"},"“Now therefore, LORD, Allah of Israel, keep with your servant Dawood my father that which you have promised him, saying,\n‘There shall not fail you a man in my sight to sit on the throne of Israel, if only your children take heed to their way, to\nwalk in my law as you have walked before me.’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CH 6:17"},"Now therefore, LORD, Allah of Israel, let your word be verified, which you spoke to your servant Dawood.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CH 6:18"},"“But will Allah indeed dwell with men on the earth? Behold, heaven and the heaven of heavens can’t contain you; how much\nless this house which I have built! \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CH 6:19"},"Yet have respect for the prayer of your servant, and to his supplication, LORD my Allah, to listen to the cry and to the\nprayer which your servant prays before you; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2CH 6:20"},"that your eyes may be open towards this house day and night, even towards the place where you have said that you would\nput your name; to listen to the prayer which your servant will pray towards this place.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2CH 6:21"},"Listen to the petitions of your servant, and of your people Israel, when they pray towards this place. Yes, hear from\nyour dwelling place, even from heaven; and when you hear, forgive.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"2CH 6:22"},"“If a man sins against his neighbour, and an oath is laid on him to cause him to swear, and he comes and swears before\nyour altar in this house; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"2CH 6:23"},"then hear from heaven, act, and judge your servants, bringing retribution to the wicked, to bring his way on his own\nhead; and justifying the righteous, to give him according to his righteousness.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"2CH 6:24"},"“If your people Israel are struck down before the enemy because they have sinned against you, and they turn again and\nconfess your name, and pray and make supplication before you in this house;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"2CH 6:25"},"then hear from heaven, and forgive the sin of your people Israel, and bring them again to the land which you gave to them\nand to their fathers. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"2CH 6:26"},"“When the sky is shut up, and there is no rain, because they have sinned against you; if they pray towards this place,\nand confess your name, and turn from their sin, when you afflict them;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"2CH 6:27"},"then hear in heaven, and forgive the sin of your servants of your people Israel, when you teach them the good way in\nwhich they should walk; and send rain on your land, which you have given to your people for an inheritance.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"2CH 6:28"},"“If there is famine in the land, if there is pestilence, if there is blight or mildew, locust or caterpillar; if their\nenemies besiege them in the land of their cities; whatever plague or whatever sickness there is;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"2CH 6:29"},"whatever prayer and supplication is made by any man, or by all your people Israel, who will each know his own plague and\nhis own sorrow, and shall spread out his hands towards this house;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"2CH 6:30"},"then hear from heaven your dwelling place and forgive, and render to every man according to all his ways, whose heart you\nknow (for you, even you only, know the hearts of the children of men)\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"2CH 6:31"},"that they may fear you, to walk in your ways, so long as they live in the land which you gave to our fathers.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"2CH 6:32"},"“Moreover concerning the foreigner, who is not of your people Israel, when he comes from a far country for your great\nname’s sake, and your mighty hand, and your outstretched arm; when they come and pray towards this house;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"2CH 6:33"},"then hear from heaven, even from your dwelling place, and do according to all that the foreigner calls to you for; that\nall the peoples of the earth may know your name and fear you, as do your people Israel, and that they may know that this house\nwhich I have built is called by your name. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"2CH 6:34"},"“If your people go out to battle against their enemies, by whatever way you send them, and they pray to you towards this\ncity which you have chosen, and the house which I have built for your name;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"2CH 6:35"},"then hear from heaven their prayer and their supplication, and maintain their cause.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"2CH 6:36"},"“If they sin against you (for there is no man who doesn’t sin), and you are angry with them, and deliver them to the\nenemy, so that they carry them away captive to a land far off or near;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"2CH 6:37"},"yet if they come to their senses in the land where they are carried captive, and turn again, and make supplication to you\nin the land of their captivity, saying, ‘We have sinned, we have done perversely, and have dealt wickedly;’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"2CH 6:38"},"if they return to you with all their heart and with all their soul in the land of their captivity, where they have\ncarried them captive, and pray towards their land, which you gave to their fathers, and the city which you have chosen, and\ntowards the house which I have built for your name; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"2CH 6:39"},"then hear from heaven, even from your dwelling place, their prayer and their petitions, and maintain their cause, and\nforgive your people who have sinned against you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"2CH 6:40"},"“Now, my Allah, let, I beg you, your eyes be open, and let your ears be attentive, to the prayer that is made in this\nplace. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"2CH 6:41"},"“Now therefore arise, Allah the LORD, into your resting place, you, and the ark of your strength. Let your priests, Allah\nthe LORD, be clothed with salvation, and let your saints rejoice in goodness.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"2CH 6:42"},"“Allah the LORD, don’t turn away the face of your anointed. Remember your loving kindnesses to Dawood your servant.”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"7","sid":"2CH 7"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 7:1"},"Now when Sulaiman had finished praying, fire came down from heaven and consumed the burnt offering and the sacrifices; and\nthe LORD’s glory filled the house. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 7:2"},"The priests could not enter into the LORD’s house, because the LORD’s glory filled the LORD’s house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 7:3"},"All the children of Israel looked on, when the fire came down, and the LORD’s glory was on the house. They bowed\nthemselves with their faces to the ground on the pavement, worshipped, and gave thanks to the LORD, saying,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“For he is good; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for his loving kindness endures forever.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 7:4"},"Then the king and all the people offered sacrifices before the LORD.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 7:5"},"King Sulaiman offered a sacrifice of twenty-two thousand head of cattle and a hundred and twenty thousand sheep. So the\nking and all the people dedicated Allah’s house. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 7:6"},"The priests stood, according to their positions; the Levites also with instruments of music of the LORD, which Dawood the\nking had made to give thanks to the LORD, when Dawood praised by their ministry, saying “For his loving kindness endures\nforever.” The priests sounded trumpets before them; and all Israel stood.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 7:7"},"Moreover Sulaiman made the middle of the court that was before the LORD’s house holy; for there he offered the burnt\nofferings, and the fat of the peace offerings, because the bronze altar which Sulaiman had made was not able to receive the\nburnt offering, the meal offering, and the fat. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 7:8"},"So Sulaiman held the feast at that time for seven days, and all Israel with him, a very great assembly, from the entrance\nof Hamath to the brook of Egypt. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 7:9"},"On the eighth day, they held a solemn assembly; for they kept the dedication of the altar seven days, and the feast seven\ndays. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 7:10"},"On the twenty-third day of the seventh month, he sent the people away to their tents, joyful and glad of heart for the\ngoodness that the LORD had shown to Dawood, and to Sulaiman, and to Israel his people.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 7:11"},"Thus Sulaiman finished the LORD’s house and the king’s house; and he successfully completed all that came into Sulaiman’s\nheart to make in the LORD’s house and in his own house. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 7:12"},"The LORD appeared to Sulaiman by night, and said to him, “I have heard your prayer, and have chosen this place for myself\nfor a house of sacrifice. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 7:13"},"“If I shut up the sky so that there is no rain, or if I command the locust to devour the land, or if I send pestilence\namongst my people; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 7:14"},"if my people, who are called by my name, will humble themselves, pray, seek my face, and turn from their wicked ways;\nthen I will hear from heaven, will forgive their sin, and will heal their land.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 7:15"},"Now my eyes will be open and my ears attentive to prayer that is made in this place.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 7:16"},"For now I have chosen and made this house holy, that my name may be there forever; and my eyes and my heart will be there\nperpetually. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CH 7:17"},"“As for you, if you will walk before me as Dawood your father walked, and do according to all that I have commanded you,\nand will keep my statutes and my ordinances; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CH 7:18"},"then I will establish the throne of your kingdom, according as I covenanted with Dawood your father, saying, ‘There shall\nnot fail you a man to be ruler in Israel.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CH 7:19"},"But if you turn away, and forsake my statutes and my commandments which I have set before you, and shall go and serve\nother gods, and worship them; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2CH 7:20"},"then I will pluck them up by the roots out of my land which I have given them; and this house, which I have made holy for\nmy name, I will cast out of my sight, and I will make it a proverb and a byword amongst all peoples.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2CH 7:21"},"This house, which is so high, everyone who passes by it shall be astonished, and shall say, ‘Why has the LORD done this\nto this land and to this house?’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"2CH 7:22"},"They shall answer, ‘Because they abandoned the LORD, Allah of their fathers, who brought them out of the land of Egypt,\nand took other gods, worshipped them, and served them. Therefore he has brought all this evil on them.’”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"8","sid":"2CH 8"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 8:1"},"At the end of twenty years, in which Sulaiman had built the LORD’s house and his own house,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 8:2"},"Sulaiman built the cities which Huram had given to Sulaiman, and caused the children of Israel to dwell there.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 8:3"},"Sulaiman went to Hamath Zobah, and prevailed against it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 8:4"},"He built Tadmor in the wilderness, and all the storage cities, which he built in Hamath.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 8:5"},"Also he built Beth Horon the upper and Beth Horon the lower, fortified cities, with walls, gates, and bars;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 8:6"},"and Baalath, and all the storage cities that Sulaiman had, and all the cities for his chariots, the cities for his\nhorsemen, and all that Sulaiman desired to build for his pleasure in Jerusalem, in Lebanon, and in all the land of his\ndominion. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 8:7"},"As for all the people who were left of the Hittites, the Amorites, the Perizzites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites, who\nwere not of Israel; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 8:8"},"of their children who were left after them in the land, whom the children of Israel didn’t consume, of them Sulaiman\nconscripted forced labour to this day. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 8:9"},"But of the children of Israel, Sulaiman made no servants for his work; but they were men of war, and chief of his\ncaptains, and rulers of his chariots and of his horsemen. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 8:10"},"These were the chief officers of king Sulaiman, even two-hundred and fifty, who ruled over the people.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 8:11"},"Sulaiman brought up Pharaoh’s daughter out of Dawood’s city to the house that he had built for her; for he said, “My wife\nshall not dwell in the house of Dawood king of Israel, because the places where the LORD’s ark has come are holy.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 8:12"},"Then Sulaiman offered burnt offerings to the LORD on the LORD’s altar, which he had built before the porch,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 8:13"},"even as the duty of every day required, offering according to the commandment of Musa, on the Sabbaths, on the new moons,\nand on the set feasts, three times per year, during the feast of unleavened bread, during the feast of weeks, and during the\nfeast of booths.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, feast of tents (Sukkot)"]}],"caller":"+"},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 8:14"},"He appointed, according to the ordinance of Dawood his father, the divisions of the priests to their service, and the\nLevites to their offices, to praise and to minister before the priests, as the duty of every day required; the doorkeepers also\nby their divisions at every gate, for Dawood the man of Allah had so commanded.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 8:15"},"They didn’t depart from the commandment of the king to the priests and Levites concerning any matter, or concerning the\ntreasures. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 8:16"},"Now all the work of Sulaiman was prepared from the day of the foundation of the LORD’s house until it was finished. So\nthe LORD’s house was completed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CH 8:17"},"Then Sulaiman went to Ezion Geber and to Eloth, on the seashore in the land of Edom.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CH 8:18"},"Huram sent him ships and servants who had knowledge of the sea by the hands of his servants; and they came with the\nservants of Sulaiman to Ophir, and brought from there four hundred and fifty\ntalents",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:18 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A talent is about 30 kilograms or 66 pounds or 965 Troy ounces, so 450 talents is about 13.5 metric\ntonnes"]}],"caller":"+"}," of gold, and brought them to king Sulaiman. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"9","sid":"2CH 9"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 9:1"},"When the queen of Sheba heard of the fame of Sulaiman, she came to test Sulaiman with hard questions at Jerusalem, with a\nvery great caravan, including camels that bore spices, gold in abundance, and precious stones. When she had come to Sulaiman,\nshe talked with him about all that was in her heart. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 9:2"},"Sulaiman answered all her questions. There wasn’t anything hidden from Sulaiman which he didn’t tell her.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 9:3"},"When the queen of Sheba had seen the wisdom of Sulaiman, the house that he had built,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 9:4"},"the food of his table, the seating of his servants, the attendance of his ministers, their clothing, his cup bearers also,\ntheir clothing, and his ascent by which he went up to the LORD’s house; there was no more spirit in\nher.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:4 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, she was breathless."]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 9:5"},"She said to the king, “It was a true report that I heard in my own land of your acts and of your wisdom.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 9:6"},"However I didn’t believe their words until I came, and my eyes had seen it; and behold half of the greatness of your\nwisdom wasn’t told me. You exceed the fame that I heard! \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 9:7"},"Happy are your men, and happy are these your servants, who stand continually before you, and hear your wisdom.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 9:8"},"Blessed be Allah your LORD, who delighted in you, to set you on his throne, to be king for Allah your LORD; because your\nAllah loved Israel, to establish them forever. Therefore he made you king over them, to do justice and righteousness.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 9:9"},"She gave the king one hundred and twenty talents",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:9\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A talent is about 30 kilograms or 66 pounds or 965 Troy ounces, so 120 talents is about 3.6 metric\ntonnes"]}],"caller":"+"}," of gold, spices in great abundance, and precious stones. There was never before such spice as the queen of Sheba gave\nto king Sulaiman. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 9:10"},"The servants of Huram and the servants of Sulaiman, who brought gold from Ophir, also brought algum\ntrees",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:10 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["possibly Indian sandalwood, which has nice grain and a pleasant scent and is good for\nwoodworking"]}],"caller":"+"}," and precious stones. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 9:11"},"The king used algum tree wood to make terraces for the LORD’s house and for the king’s house, and harps and stringed\ninstruments for the singers. There were none like these seen before in the land of Judah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 9:12"},"King Sulaiman gave to the queen of Sheba all her desire, whatever she asked, in addition to that which she had brought to\nthe king. So she turned, and went to her own land, she and her servants.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 9:13"},"Now the weight of gold that came to Sulaiman in one year was six hundred and sixty-six\ntalents",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A talent is about 30 kilograms or 66 pounds or 965 Troy ounces, so 666 talents is about 20 metric\ntonnes"]}],"caller":"+"}," of gold, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 9:14"},"in addition to that which the traders and merchants brought. All the kings of Arabia and the governors of the country\nbrought gold and silver to Sulaiman. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 9:15"},"King Sulaiman made two hundred bucklers of beaten gold. Six hundred\nshekels",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:15 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A shekel is about 10 grams or about 0.32 Troy ounces, so 600 shekels was about 6 kilograms or about\n192 Troy ounces."]}],"caller":"+"}," of beaten gold went to one buckler. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 9:16"},"He made three hundred shields of beaten gold. Three hundred\nshekels",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A shekel is about 10 grams or about 0.32 Troy ounces, so 300 shekels was about 3 kilograms or about\n96 Troy ounces."]}],"caller":"+"}," of gold went to one shield. The king put them in the House of the Forest of Lebanon.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CH 9:17"},"Moreover the king made a great throne of ivory, and overlaid it with pure gold.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CH 9:18"},"There were six steps to the throne, with a footstool of gold, which were fastened to the throne, and armrests on either\nside by the place of the seat, and two lions standing beside the armrests.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CH 9:19"},"Twelve lions stood there on the one side and on the other on the six steps. There was nothing like it made in any other\nkingdom. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2CH 9:20"},"All king Sulaiman’s drinking vessels were of gold, and all the vessels of the House of the Forest of Lebanon were of pure\ngold. Silver was not considered valuable in the days of Sulaiman.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2CH 9:21"},"For the king had ships that went to Tarshish with Huram’s servants. Once every three years, the ships of Tarshish came\nbringing gold, silver, ivory, apes, and peacocks. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"2CH 9:22"},"So king Sulaiman exceeded all the kings of the earth in riches and wisdom.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"2CH 9:23"},"All the kings of the earth sought the presence of Sulaiman, to hear his wisdom, which Allah had put in his heart.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"2CH 9:24"},"They each brought tribute, vessels of silver, vessels of gold, clothing, armour, spices, horses, and mules every year.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"2CH 9:25"},"Sulaiman had four thousand stalls for horses and chariots, and twelve thousand horsemen, that he stationed in the chariot\ncities, and with the king at Jerusalem. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"2CH 9:26"},"He ruled over all the kings from the River even to the land of the Philistines, and to the border of Egypt.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"2CH 9:27"},"The king made silver as common in Jerusalem as stones, and he made cedars to be as abundant as the sycamore trees that\nare in the lowland. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"2CH 9:28"},"They brought horses for Sulaiman out of Egypt and out of all lands.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"2CH 9:29"},"Now the rest of the acts of Sulaiman, first and last, aren’t they written in the history of Nathan the prophet, and in\nthe prophecy of Ahijah the Shilonite, and in the visions of Iddo the seer concerning Jeroboam the son of Nebat?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"2CH 9:30"},"Sulaiman reigned in Jerusalem over all Israel forty years.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"2CH 9:31"},"Sulaiman slept with his fathers, and he was buried in his father Dawood’s city: and Rehoboam his son reigned in his\nplace. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"10","sid":"2CH 10"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 10:1"},"Rehoboam went to Shechem; for all Israel had come to Shechem to make him king.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 10:2"},"When Jeroboam the son of Nebat heard of it (for he was in Egypt, where he had fled from the presence of king Sulaiman),\nJeroboam returned out of Egypt. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 10:3"},"They sent and called him; and Jeroboam and all Israel came, and they spoke to Rehoboam, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 10:4"},"“Your father made our yoke grievous: now therefore make the grievous service of your father, and his heavy yoke which he\nput on us, lighter, and we will serve you.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 10:5"},"He said to them, “Come again to me after three days.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["So the people departed. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 10:6"},"King Rehoboam took counsel with the old men, who had stood before Sulaiman his father while he yet lived, saying, “What\ncounsel do you give me about how to answer these people?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 10:7"},"They spoke to him, saying, “If you are kind to these people, please them, and speak good words to them, then they will be\nyour servants forever.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 10:8"},"But he abandoned the counsel of the old men which they had given him, and took counsel with the young men who had grown up\nwith him, who stood before him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 10:9"},"He said to them, “What counsel do you give, that we may give an answer to these people, who have spoken to me, saying,\n‘Make the yoke that your father put on us lighter?’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 10:10"},"The young men who had grown up with him spoke to him, saying, “Thus you shall tell the people who spoke to you, saying,\n‘Your father made our yoke heavy, but make it lighter on us;’ thus you shall say to them, ‘My little finger is thicker than my\nfather’s waist. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 10:11"},"Now whereas my father burdened you with a heavy yoke, I will add to your yoke. My father chastised you with whips, but I\nwill chastise you with scorpions.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 10:12"},"So Jeroboam and all the people came to Rehoboam the third day, as the king asked, saying, “Come to me again the third\nday.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 10:13"},"The king answered them roughly; and king Rehoboam abandoned the counsel of the old men,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 10:14"},"and spoke to them after the counsel of the young men, saying, “My father made your yoke heavy, but I will add to it. My\nfather chastised you with whips, but I will chastise you with scorpions.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 10:15"},"So the king didn’t listen to the people; for it was brought about by Allah, that the LORD might establish his word, which\nhe spoke by Ahijah the Shilonite to Jeroboam the son of Nebat. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 10:16"},"When all Israel saw that the king didn’t listen to them, the people answered the king, saying, “What portion do we have\nin Dawood? We don’t have an inheritance in the son of Jesse! Every man to your tents, Israel! Now see to your own house,\nDawood.” So all Israel departed to their tents. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CH 10:17"},"But as for the children of Israel who lived in the cities of Judah, Rehoboam reigned over them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CH 10:18"},"Then king Rehoboam sent Hadoram, who was over the men subject to forced labour; and the children of Israel stoned him to\ndeath with stones. King Rehoboam hurried to get himself up to his chariot, to flee to Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CH 10:19"},"So Israel rebelled against Dawood’s house to this day. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"11","sid":"2CH 11"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 11:1"},"When Rehoboam had come to Jerusalem, he assembled the house of Judah and Benjamin, one hundred and eighty thousand chosen\nmen who were warriors, to fight against Israel, to bring the kingdom again to Rehoboam.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 11:2"},"But the LORD’s word came to Shemaiah the man of Allah, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 11:3"},"“Speak to Rehoboam the son of Sulaiman, king of Judah, and to all Israel in Judah and Benjamin, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 11:4"},"‘The LORD says, “You shall not go up, nor fight against your brothers! Every man return to his house; for this thing is of\nme.”’” So they listened to the LORD’s words, and returned from going against Jeroboam.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 11:5"},"Rehoboam lived in Jerusalem, and built cities for defence in Judah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 11:6"},"He built Bethlehem, Etam, Tekoa, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 11:7"},"Beth Zur, Soco, Adullam, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 11:8"},"Gath, Mareshah, Ziph, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 11:9"},"Adoraim, Lachish, Azekah, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 11:10"},"Zorah, Aijalon, and Hebron, which are fortified cities in Judah and in Benjamin.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 11:11"},"He fortified the strongholds, and put captains in them, and stores of food, oil and wine.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 11:12"},"He put shields and spears in every city, and made them exceedingly strong. Judah and Benjamin belonged to him.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 11:13"},"The priests and the Levites who were in all Israel stood with him out of all their territory.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 11:14"},"For the Levites left their pasture lands and their possession, and came to Judah and Jerusalem; for Jeroboam and his sons\ncast them off, that they should not execute the priest’s office to the LORD.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 11:15"},"He himself appointed priests for the high places, for the male goats, and for the calves which he had made.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 11:16"},"After them, out of all the tribes of Israel, those who set their hearts to seek the LORD, Allah of Israel, came to\nJerusalem to sacrifice to the LORD, Allah of their fathers. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CH 11:17"},"So they strengthened the kingdom of Judah, and made Rehoboam the son of Sulaiman strong for three years; for they walked\nthree years in the way of Dawood and Sulaiman. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CH 11:18"},"Rehoboam took a wife for himself, Mahalath the daughter of Jerimoth the son of Dawood and of Abihail the daughter of\nEliab the son of Jesse. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CH 11:19"},"She bore him sons: Jeush, Shemariah, and Zaham. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2CH 11:20"},"After her, he took Maacah the daughter of Absalom; and she bore him Abijah, Attai, Ziza, and Shelomith.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2CH 11:21"},"Rehoboam loved Maacah the daughter of Absalom above all his wives and his concubines; for he took eighteen wives and\nsixty concubines, and became the father of twenty-eight sons and sixty daughters.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"2CH 11:22"},"Rehoboam appointed Abijah the son of Maacah to be chief, the prince amongst his brothers; for he intended to make him\nking. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"2CH 11:23"},"He dealt wisely, and dispersed of all his sons throughout all the lands of Judah and Benjamin, to every fortified city.\nHe gave them food in abundance and he sought many wives for them.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"12","sid":"2CH 12"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 12:1"},"When the kingdom of Rehoboam was established and he was strong, he abandoned the LORD’s law, and all Israel with him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 12:2"},"In the fifth year of king Rehoboam, Shishak king of Egypt came up against Jerusalem, because they had trespassed against\nthe LORD, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 12:3"},"with twelve hundred chariots, and sixty thousand horsemen. The people were without number who came with him out of Egypt:\nthe Lubim, the Sukkiim, and the Ethiopians. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 12:4"},"He took the fortified cities which belonged to Judah, and came to Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 12:5"},"Now Shemaiah the prophet came to Rehoboam, and to the princes of Judah, who were gathered together to Jerusalem because of\nShishak, and said to them, “The LORD says, ‘You have forsaken me, therefore I have also left you in the hand of Shishak.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 12:6"},"Then the princes of Israel and the king humbled themselves; and they said, “The LORD is righteous.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 12:7"},"When the LORD saw that they humbled themselves, the LORD’s word came to Shemaiah, saying, “They have humbled themselves. I\nwill not destroy them; but I will grant them some deliverance, and my wrath won’t be poured out on Jerusalem by the hand of\nShishak. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 12:8"},"Nevertheless they will be his servants, that they may know my service, and the service of the kingdoms of the countries.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 12:9"},"So Shishak king of Egypt came up against Jerusalem and took away the treasures of the LORD’s house and the treasures of\nthe king’s house. He took it all away. He also took away the shields of gold which Sulaiman had made.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 12:10"},"King Rehoboam made shields of bronze in their place, and committed them to the hands of the captains of the guard, who\nkept the door of the king’s house. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 12:11"},"As often as the king entered into the LORD’s house, the guard came and bore them, then brought them back into the guard\nroom. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 12:12"},"When he humbled himself, the LORD’s wrath turned from him, so as not to destroy him altogether. Moreover, there were good\nthings found in Judah. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 12:13"},"So king Rehoboam strengthened himself in Jerusalem and reigned; for Rehoboam was forty-one years old when he began to\nreign, and he reigned seventeen years in Jerusalem, the city which the LORD had chosen out of all the tribes of Israel to put\nhis name there. His mother’s name was Naamah the Ammonitess. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 12:14"},"He did that which was evil, because he didn’t set his heart to seek the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 12:15"},"Now the acts of Rehoboam, first and last, aren’t they written in the histories of Shemaiah the prophet and of Iddo the\nseer, in the genealogies? There were wars between Rehoboam and Jeroboam continually.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 12:16"},"Rehoboam slept with his fathers, and was buried in Dawood’s city; and Abijah his son reigned in his place.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"13","sid":"2CH 13"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 13:1"},"In the eighteenth year of king Jeroboam, Abijah began to reign over Judah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 13:2"},"He reigned three years in Jerusalem. His mother’s name was Micaiah the daughter of Uriel of Gibeah. There was war between\nAbijah and Jeroboam. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 13:3"},"Abijah joined battle with an army of valiant men of war, even four hundred thousand chosen men; and Jeroboam set the\nbattle in array against him with eight hundred thousand chosen men, who were mighty men of valour.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 13:4"},"Abijah stood up on Mount Zemaraim, which is in the hill country of Ephraim, and said, “Hear me, Jeroboam and all Israel:\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 13:5"},"Ought you not to know that the LORD, Allah of Israel, gave the kingdom over Israel to Dawood forever, even to him and to\nhis sons by a covenant of salt? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 13:6"},"Yet Jeroboam the son of Nebat, the servant of Sulaiman the son of Dawood, rose up, and rebelled against his lord.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 13:7"},"Worthless men were gathered to him, wicked fellows who strengthened themselves against Rehoboam the son of Sulaiman, when\nRehoboam was young and tender hearted, and could not withstand them.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 13:8"},"“Now you intend to withstand the kingdom of the LORD in the hand of the sons of Dawood. You are a great multitude, and the\ngolden calves which Jeroboam made you for gods are with you. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 13:9"},"Haven’t you driven out the priests of the LORD, the sons of Harun, and the Levites, and made priests for yourselves\naccording to the ways of the peoples of other lands? Whoever comes to consecrate himself with a young bull and seven rams may\nbe a priest of those who are no gods. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 13:10"},"“But as for us, the LORD is our Allah, and we have not forsaken him. We have priests serving the LORD, the sons of Harun,\nand the Levites in their work; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 13:11"},"and they burn to the LORD every morning and every evening burnt offerings and sweet incense. They also set the show bread\nin order on the pure table; and the lamp stand of gold with its lamps, to burn every evening; for we keep the instruction of\nthe LORD our Allah, but you have forsaken him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 13:12"},"Behold, Allah is with us at our head, and his priests with the trumpets of alarm to sound an alarm against you. Children\nof Israel, don’t fight against the LORD, Allah of your fathers; for you will not prosper.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 13:13"},"But Jeroboam caused an ambush to come about behind them; so they were before Judah, and the ambush was behind them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 13:14"},"When Judah looked back, behold, the battle was before and behind them; and they cried to the LORD, and the priests\nsounded with the trumpets. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 13:15"},"Then the men of Judah gave a shout. As the men of Judah shouted, Allah struck Jeroboam and all Israel before Abijah and\nJudah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 13:16"},"The children of Israel fled before Judah, and Allah delivered them into their hand.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CH 13:17"},"Abijah and his people killed them with a great slaughter, so five hundred thousand chosen men of Israel fell down slain.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CH 13:18"},"Thus the children of Israel were brought under at that time, and the children of Judah prevailed, because they relied on\nthe LORD, Allah of their fathers. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CH 13:19"},"Abijah pursued Jeroboam, and took cities from him, Bethel with its villages, Jeshanah with its villages, and Ephron with\nits villages. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2CH 13:20"},"Jeroboam didn’t recover strength again in the days of Abijah. The LORD struck him, and he died.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2CH 13:21"},"But Abijah grew mighty, and took for himself fourteen wives, and became the father of twenty-two sons, and sixteen\ndaughters. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"2CH 13:22"},"The rest of the acts of Abijah, his ways, and his sayings are written in the commentary of the prophet Iddo.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"14","sid":"2CH 14"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 14:1"},"So Abijah slept with his fathers, and they buried him in Dawood’s city; and Asa his son reigned in his place. In his days,\nthe land was quiet ten years. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 14:2"},"Asa did that which was good and right in the LORD his Allah’s eyes;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 14:3"},"for he took away the foreign altars and the high places, broke down the pillars, cut down the Asherah poles,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 14:4"},"and commanded Judah to seek the LORD, Allah of their fathers, and to obey his law and command.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 14:5"},"Also he took away out of all the cities of Judah the high places and the sun images; and the kingdom was quiet before him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 14:6"},"He built fortified cities in Judah; for the land was quiet, and he had no war in those years, because the LORD had given\nhim rest. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 14:7"},"For he said to Judah, “Let’s build these cities, and make walls around them, with towers, gates, and bars. The land is yet\nbefore us, because we have sought the LORD our Allah. We have sought him, and he has given us rest on every side.” So they\nbuilt and prospered. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 14:8"},"Asa had an army of three hundred thousand out of Judah who bore bucklers and spears, and two hundred and eighty thousand\nout of Benjamin who bore shields and drew bows. All these were mighty men of valour.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 14:9"},"Zerah the Ethiopian came out against them with an army of a million troops and three hundred chariots, and he came to\nMareshah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 14:10"},"Then Asa went out to meet him, and they set the battle in array in the valley of Zephathah at Mareshah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 14:11"},"Asa cried to the LORD his Allah, and said, “LORD, there is no one besides you to help, between the mighty and him who has\nno strength. Help us, LORD our Allah; for we rely on you, and in your name are we come against this multitude. LORD, you are\nour Allah. Don’t let man prevail against you.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 14:12"},"So the LORD struck the Ethiopians before Asa and before Judah; and the Ethiopians fled.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 14:13"},"Asa and the people who were with him pursued them to Gerar: and so many of the Ethiopians fell that they could not\nrecover themselves; for they were destroyed before the LORD and before his army; and they carried away very much booty.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 14:14"},"They struck all the cities around Gerar; for the fear of the LORD came on them, and they plundered all the cities; for\nthere was much plunder in them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 14:15"},"They also struck the tents of livestock, and carried away sheep in abundance, and camels, and returned to Jerusalem.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"15","sid":"2CH 15"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 15:1"},"The Spirit of Allah came on Azariah the son of Oded: \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 15:2"},"and he went out to meet Asa, and said to him, “Hear me, Asa, and all Judah and Benjamin! The LORD is with you, while you\nare with him; and if you seek him, he will be found by you; but if you forsake him, he will forsake you.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 15:3"},"Now for a long time Israel was without the true Allah, without a teaching priest, and without law.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 15:4"},"But when in their distress they turned to the LORD, Allah of Israel, and sought him, he was found by them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 15:5"},"In those times there was no peace to him who went out, nor to him who came in; but great troubles were on all the\ninhabitants of the lands. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 15:6"},"They were broken in pieces, nation against nation, and city against city; for Allah troubled them with all adversity.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 15:7"},"But you be strong, and don’t let your hands be slack; for your work will be rewarded.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 15:8"},"When Asa heard these words, and the prophecy of Oded the prophet, he took courage, and put away the abominations out of\nall the land of Judah and Benjamin, and out of the cities which he had taken from the hill country of Ephraim; and he renewed\nthe LORD’s altar that was before the LORD’s porch. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 15:9"},"He gathered all Judah and Benjamin, and those who lived with them out of Ephraim, Manasseh, and Simeon; for they came to\nhim out of Israel in abundance when they saw that the LORD his Allah was with him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 15:10"},"So they gathered themselves together at Jerusalem in the third month, in the fifteenth year of Asa’s reign.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 15:11"},"They sacrificed to the LORD in that day, of the plunder which they had brought, seven hundred head of cattle and seven\nthousand sheep. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 15:12"},"They entered into the covenant to seek the LORD, Allah of their fathers, with all their heart and with all their soul;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 15:13"},"and that whoever would not seek the LORD, Allah of Israel, should be put to death, whether small or great, whether man or\nwoman. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 15:14"},"They swore to the LORD with a loud voice, with shouting, with trumpets, and with cornets.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 15:15"},"All Judah rejoiced at the oath, for they had sworn with all their heart, and sought him with their whole desire; and he\nwas found by them. Then the LORD gave them rest all around. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 15:16"},"Also Maacah, the mother of Asa the king, he removed from being queen, because she had made an abominable image for an\nAsherah; so Asa cut down her image, ground it into dust, and burnt it at the brook Kidron.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CH 15:17"},"But the high places were not taken away out of Israel; nevertheless the heart of Asa was perfect all his days.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CH 15:18"},"He brought the things that his father had dedicated, and that he himself had dedicated, silver, gold, and vessels into\nAllah’s house. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CH 15:19"},"There was no more war to the thirty-fifth year of Asa’s reign.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"16","sid":"2CH 16"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 16:1"},"In the thirty-sixth year of Asa’s reign, Baasha king of Israel went up against Judah, and built Ramah, that he might not\nallow anyone to go out or come in to Asa king of Judah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 16:2"},"Then Asa brought out silver and gold out of the treasures of the LORD’s house and of the king’s house, and sent to Ben\nHadad king of Syria, who lived at Damascus, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 16:3"},"“Let there be a treaty between me and you, as there was between my father and your father. Behold, I have sent you silver\nand gold. Go, break your treaty with Baasha king of Israel, that he may depart from me.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 16:4"},"Ben Hadad listened to king Asa, and sent the captains of his armies against the cities of Israel; and they struck Ijon,\nDan, Habil Maim, and all the storage cities of Naphtali. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 16:5"},"When Baasha heard of it, he stopped building Ramah, and let his work cease.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 16:6"},"Then Asa the king took all Judah, and they carried away the stones of Rama, and its timber, with which Baasha had built;\nand he built Geba and Mizpah with them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 16:7"},"At that time Hanani the seer came to Asa king of Judah, and said to him, “Because you have relied on the king of Syria,\nand have not relied on Allah your LORD, therefore the army of the king of Syria has escaped out of your hand.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 16:8"},"Weren’t the Ethiopians and the Lubim a huge army, with chariots and exceedingly many horsemen? Yet, because you relied on\nthe LORD, he delivered them into your hand. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 16:9"},"For the LORD’s eyes run back and forth throughout the whole earth, to show himself strong in the behalf of them whose\nheart is perfect towards him. You have done foolishly in this; for from now on you will have wars.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 16:10"},"Then Asa was angry with the seer, and put him in the prison; for he was in a rage with him because of this thing. Asa\noppressed some of the people at the same time. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 16:11"},"Behold, the acts of Asa, first and last, behold, they are written in the book of the kings of Judah and Israel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 16:12"},"In the thirty-ninth year of his reign, Asa was diseased in his feet. His disease was exceedingly great: yet in his\ndisease he didn’t seek the LORD, but just the physicians. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 16:13"},"Asa slept with his fathers, and died in the forty-first year of his reign.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 16:14"},"They buried him in his own tomb, which he had dug out for himself in Dawood’s city, and laid him in the bed which was\nfilled with sweet odours and various kinds of spices prepared by the perfumers’ art; and they made a very great fire for him.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"17","sid":"2CH 17"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 17:1"},"Jehoshaphat his son reigned in his place, and strengthened himself against Israel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 17:2"},"He placed forces in all the fortified cities of Judah, and set garrisons in the land of Judah, and in the cities of\nEphraim, which Asa his father had taken. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 17:3"},"The LORD was with Jehoshaphat, because he walked in the first ways of his father Dawood, and didn’t seek the Baals,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 17:4"},"but sought to Allah of his father, and walked in his commandments, and not in the ways of Israel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 17:5"},"Therefore the LORD established the kingdom in his hand. All Judah brought tribute to Jehoshaphat, and he had riches and\nhonour in abundance. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 17:6"},"His heart was lifted up in the ways of the LORD. Furthermore, he took away the high places and the Asherah poles out of\nJudah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 17:7"},"Also in the third year of his reign he sent his princes, even Ben Hail, Obadiah, Zakariya, Nethanel, and Micaiah, to teach\nin the cities of Judah; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 17:8"},"and with them the Levites, even Shemaiah, Nethaniah, Zebadiah, Asahel, Shemiramoth, Jehonathan, Adonijah, Tobijah, and\nTobadonijah, the Levites; and with them Elishama and Jehoram, the priests.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 17:9"},"They taught in Judah, having the book of the LORD’s law with them. They went about throughout all the cities of Judah and\ntaught amongst the people. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 17:10"},"The fear of the LORD fell on all the kingdoms of the lands that were around Judah, so that they made no war against\nJehoshaphat. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 17:11"},"Some of the Philistines brought Jehoshaphat presents and silver for tribute. The Arabians also brought him flocks, seven\nthousand and seven hundred rams, and seven thousand and seven hundred male goats.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 17:12"},"Jehoshaphat grew great exceedingly; and he built fortresses and store cities in Judah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 17:13"},"He had many works in the cities of Judah; and men of war, mighty men of valour, in Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 17:14"},"This was the numbering of them according to their fathers’ houses: From Judah, the captains of thousands: Adnah the\ncaptain, and with him three hundred thousand mighty men of valour;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 17:15"},"and next to him Jehohanan the captain, and with him two hundred and eighty thousand;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 17:16"},"and next to him Amasiah the son of Zichri, who willingly offered himself to the LORD, and with him two hundred thousand\nmighty men of valour. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CH 17:17"},"From Benjamin: Eliada, a mighty man of valour, and with him two hundred thousand armed with bow and shield;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CH 17:18"},"and next to him Jehozabad, and with him one hundred and eighty thousand ready and prepared for war.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CH 17:19"},"These were those who waited on the king, in addition to those whom the king put in the fortified cities throughout all\nJudah. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"18","sid":"2CH 18"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 18:1"},"Now Jehoshaphat had riches and honour in abundance; and he allied himself with Ahab.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 18:2"},"After some years, he went down to Ahab to Samaria. Ahab killed sheep and cattle for him in abundance, and for the people\nwho were with him, and moved him to go up with him to Ramoth Gilead.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 18:3"},"Ahab king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat king of Judah, “Will you go with me to Ramoth Gilead?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He answered him, “I am as you are, and my people as your people. We will be with you in the war.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 18:4"},"Jehoshaphat said to the king of Israel, “Please enquire first for the LORD’s word.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 18:5"},"Then the king of Israel gathered the prophets together, four hundred men, and said to them, “Shall we go to Ramoth Gilead\nto battle, or shall I forbear?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They said, “Go up; for Allah will deliver it into the hand of the king.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 18:6"},"But Jehoshaphat said, “Isn’t there here a prophet of the LORD besides, that we may enquire of him?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 18:7"},"The king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, “There is yet one man by whom we may enquire of the LORD; but I hate him, for he\nnever prophesies good concerning me, but always evil. He is Micaiah the son of Imla.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Jehoshaphat said, “Don’t let the king say so.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 18:8"},"Then the king of Israel called an officer, and said, “Get Micaiah the son of Imla quickly.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 18:9"},"Now the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat the king of Judah each sat on his throne, arrayed in their robes, and they were\nsitting in an open place at the entrance of the gate of Samaria; and all the prophets were prophesying before them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 18:10"},"Zedekiah the son of Chenaanah made himself horns of iron and said, “The LORD says, ‘With these you shall push the\nSyrians, until they are consumed.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 18:11"},"All the prophets prophesied so, saying, “Go up to Ramoth Gilead, and prosper; for the LORD will deliver it into the hand\nof the king.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 18:12"},"The messenger who went to call Micaiah spoke to him, saying, “Behold, the words of the prophets declare good to the king\nwith one mouth. Let your word therefore, please be like one of theirs, and speak good.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 18:13"},"Micaiah said, “As the LORD lives, I will say what my Allah says.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 18:14"},"When he had come to the king, the king said to him, “Micaiah, shall we go to Ramoth Gilead to battle, or shall I\nforbear?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said, “Go up, and prosper. They shall be delivered into your hand.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 18:15"},"The king said to him, “How many times shall I adjure you that you speak to me nothing but the truth in the LORD’s name?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 18:16"},"He said, “I saw all Israel scattered on the mountains, as sheep that have no shepherd. The LORD said, ‘These have no\nmaster. Let them each return to his house in peace.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CH 18:17"},"The king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, “Didn’t I tell you that he would not prophesy good concerning me, but evil?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CH 18:18"},"Micaiah said, “Therefore hear the LORD’s word: I saw the LORD sitting on his throne, and all the army of heaven standing\non his right hand and on his left. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CH 18:19"},"The LORD said, ‘Who will entice Ahab king of Israel, that he may go up and fall at Ramoth Gilead?’ One spoke saying in\nthis way, and another saying in that way. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2CH 18:20"},"A spirit came out, stood before the LORD, and said, ‘I will entice him.’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“The LORD said to him, ‘How?’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2CH 18:21"},"“He said, ‘I will go, and will be a lying spirit in the mouth of all his prophets.’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“He said, ‘You will entice him, and will prevail also. Go and do so.’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"2CH 18:22"},"“Now therefore, behold, the LORD has put a lying spirit in the mouth of these your prophets; and the LORD has spoken evil\nconcerning you.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"2CH 18:23"},"Then Zedekiah the son of Chenaanah came near, and struck Micaiah on the cheek, and said, “Which way did the LORD’s Spirit\ngo from me to speak to you?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"2CH 18:24"},"Micaiah said, “Behold, you shall see on that day, when you go into an inner room to hide yourself.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"2CH 18:25"},"The king of Israel said, “Take Micaiah, and carry him back to Amon the governor of the city, and to Joash the king’s son;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"2CH 18:26"},"and say, ‘The king says, “Put this fellow in the prison, and feed him with bread of affliction and with water of\naffliction, until I return in peace.”’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"2CH 18:27"},"Micaiah said, “If you return at all in peace, the LORD has not spoken by me.” He said, “Listen, you people, all of you!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"2CH 18:28"},"So the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat the king of Judah went up to Ramoth Gilead.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"2CH 18:29"},"The king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, “I will disguise myself, and go into the battle; but you put on your robes.” So\nthe king of Israel disguised himself; and they went into the battle.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"2CH 18:30"},"Now the king of Syria had commanded the captains of his chariots, saying, “Don’t fight with small nor great, except only\nwith the king of Israel.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"2CH 18:31"},"When the captains of the chariots saw Jehoshaphat, they said, “It is the king of Israel!” Therefore they turned around to\nfight against him. But Jehoshaphat cried out, and the LORD helped him; and Allah moved them to depart from him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"2CH 18:32"},"When the captains of the chariots saw that it was not the king of Israel, they turned back from pursuing him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"2CH 18:33"},"A certain man drew his bow at random, and struck the king of Israel between the joints of the armour. Therefore he said\nto the driver of the chariot, “Turn your hand, and carry me out of the army; for I am severely wounded.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"2CH 18:34"},"The battle increased that day. However the king of Israel propped himself up in his chariot against the Syrians until the\nevening; and at about sunset, he died. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"19","sid":"2CH 19"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 19:1"},"Jehoshaphat the king of Judah returned to his house in peace to Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 19:2"},"Jehu the son of Hanani the seer went out to meet him, and said to king Jehoshaphat, “Should you help the wicked, and love\nthose who hate the LORD? Because of this, wrath is on you from before the LORD.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 19:3"},"Nevertheless there are good things found in you, in that you have put away the Asheroth out of the land, and have set your\nheart to seek Allah.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 19:4"},"Jehoshaphat lived at Jerusalem; and he went out again amongst the people from Beersheba to the hill country of Ephraim,\nand brought them back to the LORD, Allah of their fathers. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 19:5"},"He set judges in the land throughout all the fortified cities of Judah, city by city,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 19:6"},"and said to the judges, “Consider what you do, for you don’t judge for man, but for the LORD; and he is with you in the\njudgement. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 19:7"},"Now therefore let the fear of the LORD be on you. Take heed and do it; for there is no iniquity with the LORD our Allah,\nnor respect of persons, nor taking of bribes.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 19:8"},"Moreover in Jerusalem Jehoshaphat appointed Levites and priests, and of the heads of the fathers’ households of Israel,\nfor the judgement of the LORD, and for controversies. They returned to Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 19:9"},"He commanded them, saying, “You shall do this in the fear of the LORD, faithfully, and with a perfect heart.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 19:10"},"Whenever any controversy comes to you from your brothers who dwell in their cities, between blood and blood, between law\nand commandment, statutes and ordinances, you must warn them, that they not be guilty towards the LORD, and so wrath come on\nyou and on your brothers. Do this, and you will not be guilty. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 19:11"},"Behold, Amariah the chief priest is over you in all matters of the LORD; and Zebadiah the son of Ismail, the ruler of the\nhouse of Judah, in all the king’s matters. Also the Levites shall be officers before you. Deal courageously, and may the LORD\nbe with the good.” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"20","sid":"2CH 20"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 20:1"},"After this, the children of Moab, the children of Ammon, and with them some of the Ammonites, came against Jehoshaphat to\nbattle. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 20:2"},"Then some came who told Jehoshaphat, saying, “A great multitude is coming against you from beyond the sea from Syria.\nBehold, they are in Hazazon Tamar” (that is, En Gedi). \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 20:3"},"Jehoshaphat was alarmed, and set himself to seek to the LORD. He proclaimed a fast throughout all Judah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 20:4"},"Judah gathered themselves together to seek help from the LORD. They came out of all the cities of Judah to seek the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 20:5"},"Jehoshaphat stood in the assembly of Judah and Jerusalem, in the LORD’s house, before the new court;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 20:6"},"and he said, “LORD, Allah of our fathers, aren’t you Allah in heaven? Aren’t you ruler over all the kingdoms of the\nnations? Power and might are in your hand, so that no one is able to withstand you.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 20:7"},"Didn’t you, our Allah, drive out the inhabitants of this land before your people Israel, and give it to the\noffspring",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:7 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, seed"]}],"caller":"+"}," of Ibrahim your friend forever?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 20:8"},"They lived in it, and have built you a sanctuary in it for your name, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 20:9"},"‘If evil comes on us—the sword, judgement, pestilence, or famine—we will stand before this house, and before you (for your\nname is in this house), and cry to you in our affliction, and you will hear and save.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 20:10"},"Now, behold, the children of Ammon and Moab and Mount Seir, whom you would not let Israel invade when they came out of\nthe land of Egypt, but they turned away from them, and didn’t destroy them;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 20:11"},"behold, how they reward us, to come to cast us out of your possession, which you have given us to inherit.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 20:12"},"Our Allah, will you not judge them? For we have no might against this great company that comes against us. We don’t know\nwhat to do, but our eyes are on you.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 20:13"},"All Judah stood before the LORD, with their little ones, their wives, and their children.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 20:14"},"Then the LORD’s Spirit came on Jahaziel the son of Zakariya, the son of Benaiah, the son of Jeiel, the son of Mattaniah,\nthe Levite, of the sons of Asaph, in the middle of the assembly;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 20:15"},"and he said, “Listen, all Judah, and you inhabitants of Jerusalem, and you, king Jehoshaphat. The LORD says to you,\n‘Don’t be afraid, and don’t be dismayed because of this great multitude; for the battle is not yours, but Allah’s.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 20:16"},"Tomorrow, go down against them. Behold, they are coming up by the ascent of Ziz. You will find them at the end of the\nvalley, before the wilderness of Jeruel. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CH 20:17"},"You will not need to fight this battle. Set yourselves, stand still, and see the salvation of the LORD with you, O Judah\nand Jerusalem. Don’t be afraid, nor be dismayed. Go out against them tomorrow, for the LORD is with you.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CH 20:18"},"Jehoshaphat bowed his head with his face to the ground; and all Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem fell down before\nthe LORD, worshipping the LORD. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CH 20:19"},"The Levites, of the children of the Kohathites and of the children of the Korahites, stood up to praise the LORD, Allah\nof Israel, with an exceedingly loud voice. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2CH 20:20"},"They rose early in the morning, and went out into the wilderness of Tekoa. As they went out, Jehoshaphat stood and said,\n“Listen to me, Judah, and you inhabitants of Jerusalem! Believe in Allah your LORD, so you will be established! Believe his\nprophets, so you will prosper.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2CH 20:21"},"When he had taken counsel with the people, he appointed those who were to sing to the LORD, and give praise in holy\narray, as they go out before the army, and say, “Give thanks to the LORD; for his loving kindness endures forever.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"2CH 20:22"},"When they began to sing and to praise, the LORD set ambushers against the children of Ammon, Moab, and Mount Seir, who\nhad come against Judah; and they were struck. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"2CH 20:23"},"For the children of Ammon and Moab stood up against the inhabitants of Mount Seir to utterly kill and destroy them. When\nthey had finished the inhabitants of Seir, everyone helped to destroy each other.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"2CH 20:24"},"When Judah came to the place overlooking the wilderness, they looked at the multitude; and behold, they were dead bodies\nfallen to the earth, and there were none who escaped. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"2CH 20:25"},"When Jehoshaphat and his people came to take their plunder, they found amongst them in abundance both riches and dead\nbodies, and precious jewels, which they stripped off for themselves, more than they could carry away. They took plunder for\nthree days, it was so much. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"2CH 20:26"},"On the fourth day, they assembled themselves in Beracah",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:26 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["“Beracah” means “blessing”."]}],"caller":"+"}," Valley, for there they blessed the LORD. Therefore the name of that place was\ncalled “Beracah Valley” to this day. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"2CH 20:27"},"Then they returned, every man of Judah and Jerusalem, with Jehoshaphat in front of them, to go again to Jerusalem with\njoy; for the LORD had made them to rejoice over their enemies. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"2CH 20:28"},"They came to Jerusalem with stringed instruments, harps, and trumpets to the LORD’s house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"2CH 20:29"},"The fear of Allah was on all the kingdoms of the countries, when they heard that the LORD fought against the enemies of\nIsrael. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"2CH 20:30"},"So the realm of Jehoshaphat was quiet, for his Allah gave him rest all around.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"2CH 20:31"},"Jehoshaphat reigned over Judah. He was thirty-five years old when he began to reign; and he reigned twenty-five years in\nJerusalem. His mother’s name was Azubah the daughter of Shilhi. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"2CH 20:32"},"He walked in the way of Asa his father, and didn’t turn away from it, doing that which was right in the LORD’s eyes.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"2CH 20:33"},"However the high places were not taken away, and the people had still not set their hearts on Allah of their fathers.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"2CH 20:34"},"Now the rest of the acts of Jehoshaphat, first and last, behold, they are written in the history of Jehu the son of\nHanani, which is included in the book of the kings of Israel. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"2CH 20:35"},"After this, Jehoshaphat king of Judah joined himself with Ahaziah king of Israel. The same did very wickedly.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"2CH 20:36"},"He joined himself with him to make ships to go to Tarshish. They made the ships in Ezion Geber.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"2CH 20:37"},"Then Eliezer the son of Dodavahu of Mareshah prophesied against Jehoshaphat, saying, “Because you have joined yourself\nwith Ahaziah, the LORD has destroyed your works.” The ships were wrecked, so that they were not able to go to Tarshish.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"21","sid":"2CH 21"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 21:1"},"Jehoshaphat slept with his fathers, and was buried with his fathers in Dawood’s city, and Jehoram his son reigned in his\nplace. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 21:2"},"He had brothers, the sons of Jehoshaphat: Azariah, Jehiel, Zakariya, Azariah, Michael, and Shephatiah. All these were the\nsons of Jehoshaphat king of Israel. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 21:3"},"Their father gave them great gifts of silver, of gold, and of precious things, with fortified cities in Judah; but he gave\nthe kingdom to Jehoram, because he was the firstborn. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 21:4"},"Now when Jehoram had risen up over the kingdom of his father, and had strengthened himself, he killed all his brothers\nwith the sword, and also some of the princes of Israel. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 21:5"},"Jehoram was thirty-two years old when he began to reign, and he reigned eight years in Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 21:6"},"He walked in the way of the kings of Israel, as did Ahab’s house; for he had Ahab’s daughter as his wife. He did that\nwhich was evil in the LORD’s sight. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 21:7"},"However the LORD would not destroy Dawood’s house, because of the covenant that he had made with Dawood, and as he\npromised to give a lamp to him and to his children always. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 21:8"},"In his days Edom revolted from under the hand of Judah, and made a king over themselves.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 21:9"},"Then Jehoram went there with his captains and all his chariots with him. He rose up by night and struck the Edomites who\nsurrounded him, along with the captains of the chariots. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 21:10"},"So Edom revolted from under the hand of Judah to this day. Then Libnah revolted at the same time from under his hand,\nbecause he had forsaken the LORD, Allah of his fathers. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 21:11"},"Moreover he made high places in the mountains of Judah, and made the inhabitants of Jerusalem play the prostitute, and\nled Judah astray. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 21:12"},"A letter came to him from Ilyas the prophet, saying, “the LORD, Allah of Dawood your father, says, ‘Because you have not\nwalked in the ways of Jehoshaphat your father, nor in the ways of Asa king of Judah,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 21:13"},"but have walked in the way of the kings of Israel, and have made Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem to play the\nprostitute like Ahab’s house did, and also have slain your brothers of your father’s house, who were better than yourself,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 21:14"},"behold, the LORD will strike your people with a great plague, including your children, your wives, and all your\npossessions; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 21:15"},"and you will have great sickness with a disease of your bowels, until your bowels fall out by reason of the sickness, day\nby day.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 21:16"},"The LORD stirred up against Jehoram the spirit of the Philistines, and of the Arabians who are beside the Ethiopians;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CH 21:17"},"and they came up against Judah, broke into it, and carried away all the possessions that were found in the king’s house,\nincluding his sons and his wives; so that there was no son left him, except Jehoahaz, the youngest of his sons.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CH 21:18"},"After all this the LORD struck him in his bowels with an incurable disease.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CH 21:19"},"In process of time, at the end of two years, his bowels fell out by reason of his sickness, and he died of severe\ndiseases. His people made no burning for him, like the burning of his fathers.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2CH 21:20"},"He was thirty-two years old when he began to reign, and he reigned in Jerusalem eight years. He departed without being\nmissed; and they buried him in Dawood’s city, but not in the tombs of the kings.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"22","sid":"2CH 22"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 22:1"},"The inhabitants of Jerusalem made Ahaziah his youngest son king in his place, because the band of men who came with the\nArabians to the camp had slain all the oldest. So Ahaziah the son of Jehoram king of Judah reigned.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 22:2"},"Ahaziah was forty-two years old when he began to reign, and he reigned one year in Jerusalem. His mother’s name was\nAthaliah the daughter of Omri. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 22:3"},"He also walked in the ways of Ahab’s house, because his mother was his counsellor in acting wickedly.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 22:4"},"He did that which was evil in the LORD’s sight, as did Ahab’s house, for they were his counsellors after the death of his\nfather, to his destruction. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 22:5"},"He also followed their counsel, and went with Jehoram the son of Ahab king of Israel to war against Hazael king of Syria\nat Ramoth Gilead, and the Syrians wounded Joram. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 22:6"},"He returned to be healed in Jezreel of the wounds which they had given him at Ramah, when he fought against Hazael king of\nSyria. Azariah the son of Jehoram king of Judah went down to see Jehoram the son of Ahab in Jezreel, because he was sick.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 22:7"},"Now the destruction of Ahaziah was of Allah, in that he went to Joram; for when he had come, he went out with Jehoram\nagainst Jehu the son of Nimshi, whom the LORD had anointed to cut off Ahab’s house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 22:8"},"When Jehu was executing judgement on Ahab’s house, he found the princes of Judah and the sons of the brothers of Ahaziah,\nserving Ahaziah, and killed them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 22:9"},"He sought Ahaziah, and they caught him (now he was hiding in Samaria), and they brought him to Jehu, and killed him; and\nthey buried him, for they said, “He is the son of Jehoshaphat, who sought the LORD with all his heart.” The house of Ahaziah\nhad no power to hold the kingdom. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 22:10"},"Now when Athaliah the mother of Ahaziah saw that her son was dead, she arose and destroyed all the royal offspring of the\nhouse of Judah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 22:11"},"But Jehoshabeath, the king’s daughter, took Joash the son of Ahaziah, and stealthily rescued him from amongst the king’s\nsons who were slain, and put him and his nurse in the bedroom. So Jehoshabeath, the daughter of king Jehoram, the wife of\nJehoiada the priest (for she was the sister of Ahaziah), hid him from Athaliah, so that she didn’t kill him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 22:12"},"He was with them hidden in Allah’s house six years while Athaliah reigned over the land.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"23","sid":"2CH 23"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 23:1"},"In the seventh year, Jehoiada strengthened himself, and took the captains of hundreds, Azariah the son of Jeroham, Ismail\nthe son of Jehohanan, Azariah the son of Obed, Maaseiah the son of Adaiah, and Elishaphat the son of Zichri, into a covenant\nwith him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 23:2"},"They went around in Judah, and gathered the Levites out of all the cities of Judah, and the heads of fathers’ households\nof Israel, and they came to Jerusalem. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 23:3"},"All the assembly made a covenant with the king in Allah’s house. He said to them, “Behold, the king’s son must reign, as\nthe LORD has spoken concerning the sons of Dawood. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 23:4"},"This is the thing that you must do. A third part of you, who come in on the Sabbath, of the priests and of the Levites,\nshall be gatekeepers of the thresholds. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 23:5"},"A third part shall be at the king’s house; and a third part at the gate of the foundation. All the people will be in the\ncourts of the LORD’s house. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 23:6"},"But let no one come into the LORD’s house, except the priests and those who minister of the Levites. They shall come in,\nfor they are holy, but all the people shall follow the LORD’s instructions.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 23:7"},"The Levites shall surround the king, every man with his weapons in his hand. Whoever comes into the house, let him be\nslain. Be with the king when he comes in, and when he goes out.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 23:8"},"So the Levites and all Judah did according to all that Jehoiada the priest commanded: and they each took his men, those\nwho were to come in on the Sabbath; with those who were to go out on the Sabbath; for Jehoiada the priest didn’t dismiss the\nshift. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 23:9"},"Jehoiada the priest delivered to the captains of hundreds the spears, and bucklers, and shields, that had been king\nDawood’s, which were in Allah’s house. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 23:10"},"He set all the people, every man with his weapon in his hand, from the right side of the house to the left side of the\nhouse, near the altar and the house, around the king. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 23:11"},"Then they brought out the king’s son, and put the crown on him, and gave him the covenant, and made him king. Jehoiada\nand his sons anointed him, and they said, “Long live the king!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 23:12"},"When Athaliah heard the noise of the people running and praising the king, she came to the people into the LORD’s house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 23:13"},"Then she looked, and, behold, the king stood by his pillar at the entrance, and the captains and the trumpets by the\nking. All the people of the land rejoiced, and blew trumpets. The singers also played musical instruments, and led the singing\nof praise. Then Athaliah tore her clothes, and said, “Treason! treason!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 23:14"},"Jehoiada the priest brought out the captains of hundreds who were set over the army, and said to them, “Bring her out\nbetween the ranks; and whoever follows her, let him be slain with the sword.” For the priest said, “Don’t kill her in the\nLORD’s house.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 23:15"},"So they made way for her. She went to the entrance of the horse gate to the king’s house; and they killed her there.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 23:16"},"Jehoiada made a covenant between himself, all the people, and the king, that they should be the LORD’s people.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CH 23:17"},"All the people went to the house of Baal, broke it down, broke his altars and his images in pieces, and killed Mattan the\npriest of Baal before the altars. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CH 23:18"},"Jehoiada appointed the officers of the LORD’s house under the hand of the Levitical priests, whom Dawood had distributed\nin the LORD’s house, to offer the burnt offerings of the LORD, as it is written in the law of Musa, with rejoicing and with\nsinging, as Dawood had ordered. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CH 23:19"},"He set the gatekeepers at the gates of the LORD’s house, that no one who was unclean in anything should enter in.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2CH 23:20"},"He took the captains of hundreds, the nobles, the governors of the people, and all the people of the land, and brought\nthe king down from the LORD’s house. They came through the upper gate to the king’s house, and set the king on the throne of\nthe kingdom. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2CH 23:21"},"So all the people of the land rejoiced, and the city was quiet. They had slain Athaliah with the sword.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"24","sid":"2CH 24"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 24:1"},"Joash was seven years old when he began to reign, and he reigned forty years in Jerusalem. His mother’s name was Zibiah,\nof Beersheba. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 24:2"},"Joash did that which was right in the LORD’s eyes all the days of Jehoiada the priest.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 24:3"},"Jehoiada took for him two wives, and he became the father of sons and daughters.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 24:4"},"After this, Joash intended to restore the LORD’s house. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 24:5"},"He gathered together the priests and the Levites, and said to them, “Go out to the cities of Judah, and gather money to\nrepair the house of your Allah from all Israel from year to year. See that you expedite this matter.” However the Levites\ndidn’t do it right away. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 24:6"},"The king called for Jehoiada the chief, and said to him, “Why haven’t you required of the Levites to bring in the tax of\nMusa the servant of the LORD, and of the assembly of Israel, out of Judah and out of Jerusalem, for the Tent of the Testimony?”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 24:7"},"For the sons of Athaliah, that wicked woman, had broken up Allah’s house; and they also gave all the dedicated things of\nthe LORD’s house to the Baals. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 24:8"},"So the king commanded, and they made a chest, and set it outside at the gate of the LORD’s house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 24:9"},"They made a proclamation through Judah and Jerusalem, to bring in for the LORD the tax that Musa the servant of Allah laid\non Israel in the wilderness. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 24:10"},"All the princes and all the people rejoiced, and brought in, and cast into the chest, until they had filled it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 24:11"},"Whenever the chest was brought to the king’s officers by the hand of the Levites, and when they saw that there was much\nmoney, the king’s scribe and the chief priest’s officer came and emptied the chest, and took it, and carried it to its place\nagain. Thus they did day by day, and gathered money in abundance.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 24:12"},"The king and Jehoiada gave it to those who did the work of the service of the LORD’s house. They hired masons and\ncarpenters to restore the LORD’s house, and also those who worked iron and bronze to repair the LORD’s house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 24:13"},"So the workmen worked, and the work of repairing went forward in their hands. They set up Allah’s house as it was\ndesigned, and strengthened it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 24:14"},"When they had finished, they brought the rest of the money before the king and Jehoiada, from which were made vessels for\nthe LORD’s house, even vessels with which to minister and to offer, including spoons and vessels of gold and silver. They\noffered burnt offerings in the LORD’s house continually all the days of Jehoiada.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 24:15"},"But Jehoiada grew old and was full of days, and he died. He was one hundred and thirty years old when he died.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 24:16"},"They buried him in Dawood’s city amongst the kings, because he had done good in Israel, and towards Allah and his house.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CH 24:17"},"Now after the death of Jehoiada, the princes of Judah came, and bowed down to the king. Then the king listened to them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CH 24:18"},"They abandoned the house of the LORD, Allah of their fathers, and served the Asherah poles and the idols, so wrath came\non Judah and Jerusalem for this their guiltiness. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CH 24:19"},"Yet he sent prophets to them, to bring them again to the LORD, and they testified against them; but they would not\nlisten. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2CH 24:20"},"The Spirit of Allah came on Zakariya the son of Jehoiada the priest; and he stood above the people, and said to them,\n“Allah says, ‘Why do you disobey the LORD’s commandments, so that you can’t prosper? Because you have forsaken the LORD, he has\nalso forsaken you.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2CH 24:21"},"They conspired against him, and stoned him with stones at the commandment of the king in the court of the LORD’s house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"2CH 24:22"},"Thus Joash the king didn’t remember the kindness which Jehoiada his father had done to him, but killed his son. When he\ndied, he said, “May the LORD look at it, and repay it.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"2CH 24:23"},"At the end of the year, the army of the Syrians came up against him: and they came to Judah and Jerusalem, and destroyed\nall the princes of the people from amongst the people, and sent all their plunder to the king of Damascus.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"2CH 24:24"},"For the army of the Syrians came with a small company of men; and the LORD delivered a very great army into their hand,\nbecause they had forsaken the LORD, Allah of their fathers. So they executed judgement on Joash.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"2CH 24:25"},"When they had departed from him (for they left him very sick), his own servants conspired against him for the blood of\nthe sons of Jehoiada the priest, and killed him on his bed, and he died. They buried him in Dawood’s city, but they didn’t bury\nhim in the tombs of the kings. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"2CH 24:26"},"These are those who conspired against him: Zabad the son of Shimeath the Ammonitess and Jehozabad the son of Shimrith the\nMoabitess. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"2CH 24:27"},"Now concerning his sons, the greatness of the burdens laid on him, and the rebuilding of Allah’s house, behold, they are\nwritten in the commentary of the book of the kings. Amaziah his son reigned in his place.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"25","sid":"2CH 25"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 25:1"},"Amaziah was twenty-five years old when he began to reign, and he reigned twenty-nine years in Jerusalem. His mother’s name\nwas Jehoaddan, of Jerusalem. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 25:2"},"He did that which was right in the LORD’s eyes, but not with a perfect heart.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 25:3"},"Now when the kingdom was established to him, he killed his servants who had killed his father the king.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 25:4"},"But he didn’t put their children to death, but did according to that which is written in the law in the book of Musa, as\nthe LORD commanded, saying, “The fathers shall not die for the children, neither shall the children die for the fathers; but\nevery man shall die for his own sin.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 25:5"},"Moreover Amaziah gathered Judah together, and ordered them according to their fathers’ houses, under captains of thousands\nand captains of hundreds, even all Judah and Benjamin. He counted them from twenty years old and upward, and found that there\nwere three hundred thousand chosen men, able to go out to war, who could handle spear and shield.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 25:6"},"He also hired one hundred thousand mighty men of valour out of Israel for one hundred\ntalents",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["25:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A talent is about 30 kilograms or 66 pounds"]}],"caller":"+"}," of silver.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 25:7"},"A man of Allah came to him, saying, “O king, don’t let the army of Israel go with you, for the LORD is not with Israel,\nwith all the children of Ephraim. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 25:8"},"But if you will go, take action, and be strong for the battle. Allah will overthrow you before the enemy; for Allah has\npower to help, and to overthrow.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 25:9"},"Amaziah said to the man of Allah, “But what shall we do for the hundred\ntalents",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["25:9 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A talent is about 30 kilograms or 66 pounds"]}],"caller":"+"}," which I have given to the army of Israel?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The man of Allah answered, “The LORD is able to give you much more than this.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 25:10"},"Then Amaziah separated them, the army that had come to him out of Ephraim, to go home again. Therefore their anger was\ngreatly kindled against Judah, and they returned home in fierce anger.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 25:11"},"Amaziah took courage, and led his people out, and went to the Valley of Salt, and struck ten thousand of the children of\nSeir. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 25:12"},"The children of Judah carried away ten thousand alive, and brought them to the top of the rock, and threw them down from\nthe top of the rock, so that they all were broken in pieces. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 25:13"},"But the men of the army whom Amaziah sent back, that they should not go with him to battle, fell on the cities of Judah,\nfrom Samaria even to Beth Horon, and struck of them three thousand, and took much plunder.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 25:14"},"Now after Amaziah had come from the slaughter of the Edomites, he brought the gods of the children of Seir, and set them\nup to be his gods, and bowed down himself before them, and burnt incense to them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 25:15"},"Therefore the LORD’s anger burnt against Amaziah, and he sent to him a prophet, who said to him, “Why have you sought\nafter the gods of the people, which have not delivered their own people out of your hand?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 25:16"},"As he talked with him, the king said to him, “Have we made you one of the king’s counsellors? Stop! Why should you be\nstruck down?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Then the prophet stopped, and said, “I know that Allah has determined to destroy you, because you have done this, and have\nnot listened to my counsel.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CH 25:17"},"Then Amaziah king of Judah consulted his advisers, and sent to Joash, the son of Jehoahaz the son of Jehu, king of\nIsrael, saying, “Come! Let’s look one another in the face.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CH 25:18"},"Joash king of Israel sent to Amaziah king of Judah, saying, “The thistle that was in Lebanon sent to the cedar that was\nin Lebanon, saying, ‘Give your daughter to my son as his wife. Then a wild animal that was in Lebanon passed by, and trampled\ndown the thistle. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CH 25:19"},"You say to yourself that you have struck Edom; and your heart lifts you up to boast. Now stay at home. Why should you\nmeddle with trouble, that you should fall, even you, and Judah with you?’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2CH 25:20"},"But Amaziah would not listen; for it was of Allah, that he might deliver them into the hand of their enemies, because\nthey had sought after the gods of Edom. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2CH 25:21"},"So Joash king of Israel went up, and he and Amaziah king of Judah looked one another in the face at Beth Shemesh, which\nbelongs to Judah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"2CH 25:22"},"Judah was defeated by Israel; so every man fled to his tent.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"2CH 25:23"},"Joash king of Israel took Amaziah king of Judah, the son of Joash the son of Jehoahaz, at Beth Shemesh, and brought him\nto Jerusalem, and broke down the wall of Jerusalem from the gate of Ephraim to the corner gate, four hundred\ncubits.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["25:23 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A cubit is the length from the tip of the middle finger to the elbow on a man’s arm, or about 18\ninches or 46 centimetres, so 400 cubits is about 200 yards or 184\nmetres."]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"2CH 25:24"},"He took all the gold and silver, and all the vessels that were found in Allah’s house with Obed-Edom, and the treasures\nof the king’s house, the hostages also, and returned to Samaria.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"2CH 25:25"},"Amaziah the son of Joash king of Judah lived for fifteen years after the death of Joash son of Jehoahaz king of Israel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"2CH 25:26"},"Now the rest of the acts of Amaziah, first and last, behold, aren’t they written in the book of the kings of Judah and\nIsrael? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"2CH 25:27"},"Now from the time that Amaziah turned away from following the LORD, they made a conspiracy against him in Jerusalem. He\nfled to Lachish, but they sent after him to Lachish, and killed him there.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"2CH 25:28"},"They brought him on horses, and buried him with his fathers in the City of Judah.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"26","sid":"2CH 26"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 26:1"},"All the people of Judah took Uzziah, who was sixteen years old, and made him king in the place of his father Amaziah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 26:2"},"He built Eloth, and restored it to Judah, after that the king slept with his fathers.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 26:3"},"Uzziah was sixteen years old when he began to reign; and he reigned fifty-two years in Jerusalem. His mother’s name was\nJechiliah, of Jerusalem. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 26:4"},"He did that which was right in the LORD’s eyes, according to all that his father Amaziah had done.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 26:5"},"He set himself to seek Allah in the days of Zakariya, who had understanding in the vision of Allah; and as long as he\nsought the LORD, Allah made him prosper. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 26:6"},"He went out and fought against the Philistines, and broke down the wall of Gath, the wall of Jabneh, and the wall of\nAshdod; and he built cities in the country of Ashdod, and amongst the Philistines.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 26:7"},"Allah helped him against the Philistines, and against the Arabians who lived in Gur Baal, and the Meunim.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 26:8"},"The Ammonites gave tribute to Uzziah. His name spread abroad even to the entrance of Egypt; for he grew exceedingly\nstrong. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 26:9"},"Moreover Uzziah built towers in Jerusalem at the corner gate, at the valley gate, and at the turning of the wall, and\nfortified them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 26:10"},"He built towers in the wilderness, and dug out many cisterns, for he had much livestock; in the lowland also, and in the\nplain. He had farmers and vineyard keepers in the mountains and in the fruitful fields, for he loved farming.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 26:11"},"Moreover Uzziah had an army of fighting men, who went out to war by bands, according to the number of their reckoning\nmade by Jeiel the scribe and Maaseiah the officer, under the hand of Hananiah, one of the king’s captains.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 26:12"},"The whole number of the heads of fathers’ households, even the mighty men of valour, was two thousand and six hundred.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 26:13"},"Under their hand was an army, three hundred and seven thousand and five hundred, who made war with mighty power, to help\nthe king against the enemy. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 26:14"},"Uzziah prepared for them, even for all the army, shields, spears, helmets, coats of mail, bows, and stones for slinging.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 26:15"},"In Jerusalem, he made devices, invented by skilful men, to be on the towers and on the battlements, with which to shoot\narrows and great stones. His name spread far abroad, because he was marvellously helped until he was strong.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 26:16"},"But when he was strong, his heart was lifted up, so that he did corruptly, and he trespassed against the LORD his Allah;\nfor he went into the LORD’s temple to burn incense on the altar of incense.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CH 26:17"},"Azariah the priest went in after him, and with him eighty priests of the LORD, who were valiant men.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CH 26:18"},"They resisted Uzziah the king, and said to him, “It isn’t for you, Uzziah, to burn incense to the LORD, but for the\npriests the sons of Harun, who are consecrated to burn incense. Go out of the sanctuary, for you have trespassed. It will not\nbe for your honour from the LORD Allah.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CH 26:19"},"Then Uzziah was angry. He had a censer in his hand to burn incense, and while he was angry with the priests, the leprosy\nbroke out on his forehead before the priests in the LORD’s house, beside the altar of incense.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2CH 26:20"},"Azariah the chief priest, and all the priests, looked at him, and behold, he was leprous in his forehead, and they thrust\nhim out quickly from there. Yes, he himself also hurried to go out, because the LORD had struck him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2CH 26:21"},"Uzziah the king was a leper to the day of his death, and lived in a separate house, being a leper; for he was cut off\nfrom the LORD’s house. Jotham his son was over the king’s house, judging the people of the land.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"2CH 26:22"},"Now the rest of the acts of Uzziah, first and last, Isaiah the prophet, the son of Amoz, wrote.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"2CH 26:23"},"So Uzziah slept with his fathers; and they buried him with his fathers in the field of burial which belonged to the\nkings, for they said, “He is a leper.” Jotham his son reigned in his place.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"27","sid":"2CH 27"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 27:1"},"Jotham was twenty-five years old when he began to reign, and he reigned sixteen years in Jerusalem. His mother’s name was\nJerushah the daughter of Zadok. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 27:2"},"He did that which was right in the LORD’s eyes, according to all that his father Uzziah had done. However he didn’t enter\ninto the LORD’s temple. The people still acted corruptly. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 27:3"},"He built the upper gate of the LORD’s house, and he built much on the wall of Ophel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 27:4"},"Moreover he built cities in the hill country of Judah, and in the forests he built fortresses and towers.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 27:5"},"He also fought with the king of the children of Ammon, and prevailed against them. The children of Ammon gave him the same\nyear one hundred talents",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["27:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A talent is about 30 kilograms or 66\npounds"]}],"caller":"+"}," of silver, ten thousand cors",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["27:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["1 cor is the same as a homer, or about 55.9 U. S. gallons (liquid) or\n211 litres or 6 bushels. 10,000 cors of wheat would weigh about 1,640 metric\ntonnes."]}],"caller":"+"}," of wheat, and ten thousand cors of barley.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["27:5\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["10,000 cors of barley would weigh about 1,310 metric tonnes."]}],"caller":"+"}," The children of Ammon also gave that much to him in the\nsecond year, and in the third. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 27:6"},"So Jotham became mighty, because he ordered his ways before the LORD his Allah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 27:7"},"Now the rest of the acts of Jotham, and all his wars, and his ways, behold, they are written in the book of the kings of\nIsrael and Judah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 27:8"},"He was five and twenty years old when he began to reign, and reigned sixteen years in Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 27:9"},"Jotham slept with his fathers, and they buried him in Dawood’s city; and Ahaz his son reigned in his place.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"28","sid":"2CH 28"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 28:1"},"Ahaz was twenty years old when he began to reign, and he reigned sixteen years in Jerusalem. He didn’t do that which was\nright in the LORD’s eyes, like Dawood his father, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 28:2"},"but he walked in the ways of the kings of Israel, and also made molten images for the Baals.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 28:3"},"Moreover he burnt incense in the valley of the son of Hinnom, and burnt his children in the fire, according to the\nabominations of the nations whom the LORD cast out before the children of Israel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 28:4"},"He sacrificed and burnt incense in the high places, and on the hills, and under every green tree.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 28:5"},"Therefore the LORD his Allah delivered him into the hand of the king of Syria. They struck him, and carried away from him\na great multitude of captives, and brought them to Damascus. He was also delivered into the hand of the king of Israel, who\nstruck him with a great slaughter. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 28:6"},"For Pekah the son of Remaliah killed in Judah one hundred and twenty thousand in one day, all of them valiant men, because\nthey had forsaken the LORD, Allah of their fathers. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 28:7"},"Zichri, a mighty man of Ephraim, killed Maaseiah the king’s son, Azrikam the ruler of the house, and Elkanah who was next\nto the king. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 28:8"},"The children of Israel carried away captive of their brothers two hundred thousand women, sons, and daughters, and also\ntook away much plunder from them, and brought the plunder to Samaria.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 28:9"},"But a prophet of the LORD was there, whose name was Oded; and he went out to meet the army that came to Samaria, and said\nto them, “Behold, because the LORD, Allah of your fathers, was angry with Judah, he has delivered them into your hand, and you\nhave slain them in a rage which has reached up to heaven. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 28:10"},"Now you intend to degrade the children of Judah and Jerusalem as male and female slaves for yourselves. Aren’t there even\nwith you trespasses of your own against Allah your LORD? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 28:11"},"Now hear me therefore, and send back the captives that you have taken captive from your brothers, for the fierce wrath of\nthe LORD is on you.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 28:12"},"Then some of the heads of the children of Ephraim, Azariah the son of Johanan, Berechiah the son of Meshillemoth,\nJehizkiah the son of Shallum, and Amasa the son of Hadlai, stood up against those who came from the war,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 28:13"},"and said to them, “You must not bring in the captives here, for you intend that which will bring on us a trespass against\nthe LORD, to add to our sins and to our guilt; for our guilt is great, and there is fierce wrath against Israel.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 28:14"},"So the armed men left the captives and the plunder before the princes and all the assembly.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 28:15"},"The men who have been mentioned by name rose up and took the captives, and with the plunder clothed all who were naked\namongst them, dressed them, gave them sandals, and gave them something to eat and to drink, anointed them, carried all the\nfeeble of them on donkeys, and brought them to Jericho, the city of palm trees, to their brothers. Then they returned to\nSamaria. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 28:16"},"At that time king Ahaz sent to the kings of Assyria to help him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CH 28:17"},"For again the Edomites had come and struck Judah, and carried away captives.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CH 28:18"},"The Philistines also had invaded the cities of the lowland, and of the South of Judah, and had taken Beth Shemesh,\nAijalon, Gederoth, Soco with its villages, Timnah with its villages, and also Gimzo and its villages; and they lived there.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CH 28:19"},"For the LORD brought Judah low because of Ahaz king of Israel, because he acted without restraint in Judah and trespassed\nseverely against the LORD. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2CH 28:20"},"Tilgath Pilneser king of Assyria came to him, and gave him trouble, but didn’t strengthen him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2CH 28:21"},"For Ahaz took away a portion out of the LORD’s house, and out of the house of the king and of the princes, and gave it to\nthe king of Assyria; but it didn’t help him. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"2CH 28:22"},"In the time of his distress, he trespassed yet more against the LORD, this same king Ahaz.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"2CH 28:23"},"For he sacrificed to the gods of Damascus, which struck him. He said, “Because the gods of the kings of Syria helped\nthem, so I will sacrifice to them, that they may help me.” But they were the ruin of him, and of all Israel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"2CH 28:24"},"Ahaz gathered together the vessels of Allah’s house, and cut the vessels of Allah’s house in pieces, and shut up the\ndoors of the LORD’s house; and he made himself altars in every corner of Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"2CH 28:25"},"In every city of Judah he made high places to burn incense to other gods, and provoked the LORD, Allah of his fathers, to\nanger. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"2CH 28:26"},"Now the rest of his acts, and all his ways, first and last, behold, they are written in the book of the kings of Judah\nand Israel. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"2CH 28:27"},"Ahaz slept with his fathers, and they buried him in the city, even in Jerusalem, because they didn’t bring him into the\ntombs of the kings of Israel; and Hezekiah his son reigned in his place.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"29","sid":"2CH 29"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 29:1"},"Hezekiah began to reign when he was twenty-five years old, and he reigned twenty-nine years in Jerusalem. His mother’s\nname was Abijah, the daughter of Zakariya. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 29:2"},"He did that which was right in the LORD’s eyes, according to all that Dawood his father had done.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 29:3"},"In the first year of his reign, in the first month, he opened the doors of the LORD’s house, and repaired them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 29:4"},"He brought in the priests and the Levites, and gathered them together into the wide place on the east,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 29:5"},"and said to them, “Listen to me, you Levites! Now sanctify yourselves, and sanctify the LORD, Allah of your fathers’\nhouse, and carry the filthiness out of the holy place. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 29:6"},"For our fathers were unfaithful, and have done that which was evil in the LORD our Allah’s sight, and have forsaken him,\nand have turned away their faces from the habitation of the LORD, and turned their backs.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 29:7"},"Also they have shut up the doors of the porch, and put out the lamps, and have not burnt incense nor offered burnt\nofferings in the holy place to Allah of Israel. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 29:8"},"Therefore the LORD’s wrath was on Judah and Jerusalem, and he has delivered them to be tossed back and forth, to be an\nastonishment, and a hissing, as you see with your eyes. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 29:9"},"For, behold, our fathers have fallen by the sword, and our sons and our daughters and our wives are in captivity for this.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 29:10"},"Now it is in my heart to make a covenant with the LORD, Allah of Israel, that his fierce anger may turn away from us.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 29:11"},"My sons, don’t be negligent now; for the LORD has chosen you to stand before him, to minister to him, and that you should\nbe his ministers, and burn incense.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 29:12"},"Then the Levites arose, Mahath, the son of Amasai, and Joel the son of Azariah, of the sons of the Kohathites; and of the\nsons of Merari, Kish the son of Abdi, and Azariah the son of Jehallelel; and of the Gershonites, Joah the son of Zimmah, and\nEden the son of Joah; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 29:13"},"and of the sons of Elizaphan, Shimri and Jeuel; and of the sons of Asaph, Zakariya and Mattaniah;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 29:14"},"and of the sons of Heman, Jehuel and Shimei; and of the sons of Jeduthun, Shemaiah and Uzziel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 29:15"},"They gathered their brothers, sanctified themselves, and went in, according to the commandment of the king by the LORD’s\nwords, to cleanse the LORD’s house. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 29:16"},"The priests went into the inner part of the LORD’s house to cleanse it, and brought out all the uncleanness that they\nfound in the LORD’s temple into the court of the LORD’s house. The Levites took it from there to carry it out to the brook\nKidron. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CH 29:17"},"Now they began on the first day of the first month to sanctify, and on the eighth day of the month they came to the\nLORD’s porch. They sanctified the LORD’s house in eight days, and on the sixteenth day of the first month they finished.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CH 29:18"},"Then they went in to Hezekiah the king within the palace, and said, “We have cleansed all the LORD’s house, including the\naltar of burnt offering with all its vessels, and the table of show bread with all its vessels.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CH 29:19"},"Moreover have we prepared and sanctified all the vessels which king Ahaz threw away in his reign, when he was unfaithful.\nBehold, they are before the LORD’s altar.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2CH 29:20"},"Then Hezekiah the king arose early, gathered the princes of the city, and went up to the LORD’s house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2CH 29:21"},"They brought seven bulls, seven rams, seven lambs, and seven male goats, for a sin offering for the kingdom, for the\nsanctuary, and for Judah. He commanded the priests the sons of Harun to offer them on the LORD’s altar.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"2CH 29:22"},"So they killed the bulls, and the priests received the blood, and sprinkled it on the altar. They killed the rams, and\nsprinkled the blood on the altar. They also killed the lambs, and sprinkled the blood on the altar.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"2CH 29:23"},"They brought near the male goats for the sin offering before the king and the assembly; and they laid their hands on\nthem. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"2CH 29:24"},"Then the priests killed them, and they made a sin offering with their blood on the altar, to make atonement for all\nIsrael; for the king commanded that the burnt offering and the sin offering should be made for all Israel.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"2CH 29:25"},"He set the Levites in the LORD’s house with cymbals, with stringed instruments, and with harps, according to the\ncommandment of Dawood, of Gad the king’s seer, and Nathan the prophet; for the commandment was from the LORD by his prophets.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"2CH 29:26"},"The Levites stood with Dawood’s instruments, and the priests with the trumpets.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"2CH 29:27"},"Hezekiah commanded them to offer the burnt offering on the altar. When the burnt offering began, the LORD’s song also\nbegan, along with the trumpets and Dawood king of Israel’s instruments.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"2CH 29:28"},"All the assembly worshipped, the singers sang, and the trumpeters sounded. All this continued until the burnt offering\nwas finished. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"2CH 29:29"},"When they had finished offering, the king and all who were present with him bowed themselves and worshipped.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"2CH 29:30"},"Moreover Hezekiah the king and the princes commanded the Levites to sing praises to the LORD with the words of Dawood,\nand of Asaph the seer. They sang praises with gladness, and they bowed their heads and worshipped.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"2CH 29:31"},"Then Hezekiah answered, “Now you have consecrated yourselves to the LORD. Come near and bring sacrifices and thank\nofferings into the LORD’s house.” The assembly brought in sacrifices and thank offerings, and as many as were of a willing\nheart brought burnt offerings. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"2CH 29:32"},"The number of the burnt offerings which the assembly brought was seventy bulls, one hundred rams, and two hundred lambs.\nAll these were for a burnt offering to the LORD. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"2CH 29:33"},"The consecrated things were six hundred head of cattle and three thousand sheep.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"2CH 29:34"},"But the priests were too few, so that they could not skin all the burnt offerings. Therefore their brothers the Levites\nhelped them, until the work was ended, and until the priests had sanctified themselves; for the Levites were more upright in\nheart to sanctify themselves than the priests. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"2CH 29:35"},"Also the burnt offerings were in abundance, with the fat of the peace offerings, and with the drink offerings for every\nburnt offering. So the service of the LORD’s house was set in order.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"2CH 29:36"},"Hezekiah and all the people rejoiced, because of that which Allah had prepared for the people; for the thing was done\nsuddenly. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"30","sid":"2CH 30"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 30:1"},"Hezekiah sent to all Israel and Judah, and wrote letters also to Ephraim and Manasseh, that they should come to the LORD’s\nhouse at Jerusalem, to keep the Passover to the LORD, Allah of Israel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 30:2"},"For the king had taken counsel with his princes and all the assembly in Jerusalem to keep the Passover in the second\nmonth. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 30:3"},"For they could not keep it at that time, because the priests had not sanctified themselves in sufficient number, and the\npeople had not gathered themselves together to Jerusalem. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 30:4"},"The thing was right in the eyes of the king and of all the assembly.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 30:5"},"So they established a decree to make proclamation throughout all Israel, from Beersheba even to Dan, that they should come\nto keep the Passover to the LORD, Allah of Israel, at Jerusalem, for they had not kept it in great numbers in the way it is\nwritten. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 30:6"},"So the couriers went with the letters from the king and his princes throughout all Israel and Judah, and according to the\ncommandment of the king, saying, “You children of Israel, turn again to the LORD, Allah of Ibrahim, Isḥāq, and Israel, that he\nmay return to the remnant of you that have escaped out of the hand of the kings of Assyria.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 30:7"},"Don’t be like your fathers and like your brothers, who trespassed against the LORD, Allah of their fathers, so that he\ngave them up to desolation, as you see. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 30:8"},"Now don’t be stiff-necked, as your fathers were, but yield yourselves to the LORD, and enter into his sanctuary, which he\nhas sanctified forever, and serve Allah your LORD, that his fierce anger may turn away from you.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 30:9"},"For if you turn again to the LORD, your brothers and your children will find compassion before those who led them captive,\nand will come again into this land, because Allah your LORD is gracious and merciful, and will not turn away his face from you,\nif you return to him.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 30:10"},"So the couriers passed from city to city through the country of Ephraim and Manasseh, even to Zebulun, but people\nridiculed them and mocked them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 30:11"},"Nevertheless some men of Asher, Manasseh, and Zebulun humbled themselves, and came to Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 30:12"},"Also the hand of Allah came on Judah to give them one heart, to do the commandment of the king and of the princes by the\nLORD’s word. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 30:13"},"Many people assembled at Jerusalem to keep the feast of unleavened bread in the second month, a very great assembly.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 30:14"},"They arose and took away the altars that were in Jerusalem, and they took away all the altars for incense and threw them\ninto the brook Kidron. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 30:15"},"Then they killed the Passover on the fourteenth day of the second month. The priests and the Levites were ashamed, and\nsanctified themselves, and brought burnt offerings into the LORD’s house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 30:16"},"They stood in their place after their order, according to the law of Musa the man of Allah. The priests sprinkled the\nblood which they received of the hand of the Levites. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CH 30:17"},"For there were many in the assembly who had not sanctified themselves: therefore the Levites were in charge of killing\nthe Passovers for everyone who was not clean, to sanctify them to the LORD.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CH 30:18"},"For a multitude of the people, even many of Ephraim, Manasseh, Issachar, and Zebulun, had not cleansed themselves, yet\nthey ate the Passover other than the way it is written. For Hezekiah had prayed for them, saying, “May the good the LORD pardon\neveryone \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CH 30:19"},"who sets his heart to seek Allah, the LORD, Allah of his fathers, even if they aren’t clean according to the purification\nof the sanctuary.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2CH 30:20"},"The LORD listened to Hezekiah, and healed the people. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2CH 30:21"},"The children of Israel who were present at Jerusalem kept the feast of unleavened bread seven days with great gladness.\nThe Levites and the priests praised the LORD day by day, singing with loud instruments to the LORD.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"2CH 30:22"},"Hezekiah spoke encouragingly to all the Levites who had good understanding in the service of the LORD. So they ate\nthroughout the feast for the seven days, offering sacrifices of peace offerings, and making confession to the LORD, Allah of\ntheir fathers. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"2CH 30:23"},"The whole assembly took counsel to keep another seven days, and they kept another seven days with gladness.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"2CH 30:24"},"For Hezekiah king of Judah gave to the assembly for offerings one thousand bulls and seven thousand sheep; and the\nprinces gave to the assembly a thousand bulls and ten thousand sheep: and a great number of priests sanctified themselves.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"2CH 30:25"},"All the assembly of Judah, with the priests and the Levites, and all the assembly who came out of Israel, and the\nforeigners who came out of the land of Israel, and who lived in Judah, rejoiced.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"2CH 30:26"},"So there was great joy in Jerusalem; for since the time of Sulaiman the son of Dawood king of Israel there was nothing\nlike this in Jerusalem. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"2CH 30:27"},"Then the Levitical priests arose and blessed the people. Their voice was heard, and their prayer came up to his holy\nhabitation, even to heaven. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"31","sid":"2CH 31"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 31:1"},"Now when all this was finished, all Israel who were present went out to the cities of Judah, and broke the pillars in\npieces, cut down the Asherah poles, and broke down the high places and the altars out of all Judah and Benjamin, also in\nEphraim and Manasseh, until they had destroyed them all. Then all the children of Israel returned, every man to his possession,\ninto their own cities. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 31:2"},"Hezekiah appointed the divisions of the priests and the Levites after their divisions, every man according to his service,\nboth the priests and the Levites, for burnt offerings and for peace offerings, to minister, to give thanks, and to praise in\nthe gates of the LORD’s camp. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 31:3"},"He also appointed the king’s portion of his possessions for the burnt offerings, for the morning and evening burnt\nofferings, and the burnt offerings for the Sabbaths, for the new moons, and for the set feasts, as it is written in the LORD’s\nlaw. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 31:4"},"Moreover he commanded the people who lived in Jerusalem to give the portion of the priests and the Levites, that they\nmight give themselves to the LORD’s law. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 31:5"},"As soon as the commandment went out, the children of Israel gave in abundance the first fruits of grain, new wine, oil,\nhoney, and of all the increase of the field; and they brought in the tithe of all things abundantly.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 31:6"},"The children of Israel and Judah, who lived in the cities of Judah, also brought in the tithe of cattle and sheep, and the\ntithe of dedicated things which were consecrated to the LORD their Allah, and laid them in heaps.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 31:7"},"In the third month they began to lay the foundation of the heaps, and finished them in the seventh month.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 31:8"},"When Hezekiah and the princes came and saw the heaps, they blessed the LORD and his people Israel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 31:9"},"Then Hezekiah questioned the priests and the Levites about the heaps.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 31:10"},"Azariah the chief priest, of the house of Zadok, answered him and said, “Since people began to bring the offerings into\nthe LORD’s house, we have eaten and had enough, and have plenty left over, for the LORD has blessed his people; and that which\nis left is this great store.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 31:11"},"Then Hezekiah commanded them to prepare rooms in the LORD’s house, and they prepared them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 31:12"},"They brought in the offerings, the tithes, and the dedicated things faithfully. Conaniah the Levite was ruler over them,\nand Shimei his brother was second. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 31:13"},"Jehiel, Azaziah, Nahath, Asahel, Jerimoth, Jozabad, Eliel, Ismachiah, Mahath, and Benaiah were overseers under the hand\nof Conaniah and Shimei his brother, by the appointment of Hezekiah the king and Azariah the ruler of Allah’s house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 31:14"},"Kore the son of Imnah the Levite, the gatekeeper at the east gate, was over the free will offerings of Allah, to\ndistribute the LORD’s offerings and the most holy things. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 31:15"},"Under him were Eden, Miniamin, Jeshua, Shemaiah, Amariah, and Shecaniah, in the cities of the priests, in their office of\ntrust, to give to their brothers by divisions, to the great as well as to the small;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 31:16"},"in addition to those who were listed by genealogy of males, from three years old and upward, even everyone who entered\ninto the LORD’s house, as the duty of every day required, for their service in their offices according to their divisions;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CH 31:17"},"and those who were listed by genealogy of the priests by their fathers’ houses, and the Levites from twenty years old and\nupward, in their offices by their divisions; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CH 31:18"},"and those who were listed by genealogy of all their little ones, their wives, their sons, and their daughters, through\nall the congregation; for in their office of trust they sanctified themselves in holiness.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CH 31:19"},"Also for the sons of Harun the priests, who were in the fields of the pasture lands of their cities, in every city, there\nwere men who were mentioned by name, to give portions to all the males amongst the priests, and to all who were listed by\ngenealogy amongst the Levites. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2CH 31:20"},"Hezekiah did so throughout all Judah; and he did that which was good, right, and faithful before the LORD his Allah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2CH 31:21"},"In every work that he began in the service of Allah’s house, in the law, and in the commandments, to seek his Allah, he\ndid it with all his heart, and prospered. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"32","sid":"2CH 32"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 32:1"},"After these things and this faithfulness, Sennacherib king of Assyria came, entered into Judah, and encamped against the\nfortified cities, and intended to win them for himself. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 32:2"},"When Hezekiah saw that Sennacherib had come, and that he was planning to fight against Jerusalem,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 32:3"},"he took counsel with his princes and his mighty men to stop the waters of the springs which were outside of the city, and\nthey helped him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 32:4"},"So, many people gathered together and they stopped all the springs and the brook that flowed through the middle of the\nland, saying, “Why should the kings of Assyria come, and find abundant water?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 32:5"},"He took courage, built up all the wall that was broken down, and raised it up to the towers, with the other wall outside,\nand strengthened Millo in Dawood’s city, and made weapons and shields in abundance.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 32:6"},"He set captains of war over the people, and gathered them together to him in the wide place at the gate of the city, and\nspoke encouragingly to them, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 32:7"},"“Be strong and courageous. Don’t be afraid or dismayed because of the king of Assyria, nor for all the multitude who is\nwith him; for there is a greater one with us than with him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 32:8"},"An arm of flesh is with him, but the LORD our Allah is with us to help us and to fight our battles.” The people rested\nthemselves on the words of Hezekiah king of Judah. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 32:9"},"After this, Sennacherib king of Assyria sent his servants to Jerusalem, (now he was before Lachish, and all his power with\nhim), to Hezekiah king of Judah, and to all Judah who were at Jerusalem, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 32:10"},"Sennacherib king of Assyria says, “In whom do you trust, that you remain under siege in Jerusalem?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 32:11"},"Doesn’t Hezekiah persuade you, to give you over to die by famine and by thirst, saying, ‘The LORD our Allah will deliver\nus out of the hand of the king of Assyria?’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 32:12"},"Hasn’t the same Hezekiah taken away his high places and his altars, and commanded Judah and Jerusalem, saying, ‘You shall\nworship before one altar, and you shall burn incense on it?’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 32:13"},"Don’t you know what I and my fathers have done to all the peoples of the lands? Were the gods of the nations of the lands\nin any way able to deliver their land out of my hand? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 32:14"},"Who was there amongst all the gods of those nations which my fathers utterly destroyed, that could deliver his people out\nof my hand, that your Allah should be able to deliver you out of my hand?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 32:15"},"Now therefore don’t let Hezekiah deceive you, nor persuade you in this way. Don’t believe him, for no god of any nation\nor kingdom was able to deliver his people out of my hand, and out of the hand of my fathers. How much less will your Allah\ndeliver you out of my hand?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 32:16"},"His servants spoke yet more against the LORD Allah, and against his servant Hezekiah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CH 32:17"},"He also wrote letters insulting the LORD, Allah of Israel, and speaking against him, saying, “As the gods of the nations\nof the lands, which have not delivered their people out of my hand, so shall Allah of Hezekiah not deliver his people out of my\nhand.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CH 32:18"},"They called out with a loud voice in the Jews’ language to the people of Jerusalem who were on the wall, to frighten\nthem, and to trouble them; that they might take the city. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CH 32:19"},"They spoke of Allah of Jerusalem as of the gods of the peoples of the earth, which are the work of men’s hands.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2CH 32:20"},"Hezekiah the king and Isaiah the prophet the son of Amoz, prayed because of this, and cried to heaven.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2CH 32:21"},"The LORD sent an angel, who cut off all the mighty men of valour, and the leaders and captains, in the camp of the king\nof Assyria. So he returned with shame of face to his own land. When he had come into the house of his god, those who came out\nof his own body",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["32:21 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["i.e., his own sons"]}],"caller":"+"}," killed him there with the sword.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"2CH 32:22"},"Thus the LORD saved Hezekiah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem from the hand of Sennacherib the king of Assyria and from\nthe hand of all others, and guided them on every side. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"2CH 32:23"},"Many brought gifts to the LORD to Jerusalem, and precious things to Hezekiah king of Judah; so that he was exalted in the\nsight of all nations from then on. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"2CH 32:24"},"In those days Hezekiah was terminally ill, and he prayed to the LORD; and he spoke to him, and gave him a sign.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"2CH 32:25"},"But Hezekiah didn’t reciprocate appropriate to the benefit done for him, because his heart was lifted up. Therefore there\nwas wrath on him, and on Judah and Jerusalem. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"2CH 32:26"},"Notwithstanding Hezekiah humbled himself for the pride of his heart, both he and the inhabitants of Jerusalem, so that\nthe LORD’s wrath didn’t come on them in the days of Hezekiah. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"2CH 32:27"},"Hezekiah had exceedingly much riches and honour. He provided himself with treasuries for silver, for gold, for precious\nstones, for spices, for shields, and for all kinds of valuable vessels;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"2CH 32:28"},"also storehouses for the increase of grain, new wine, and oil; and stalls for all kinds of animals, and flocks in folds.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"2CH 32:29"},"Moreover he provided for himself cities, and possessions of flocks and herds in abundance; for Allah had given him\nabundant possessions. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"2CH 32:30"},"This same Hezekiah also stopped the upper spring of the waters of Gihon, and brought them straight down on the west side\nof Dawood’s city. Hezekiah prospered in all his works. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"2CH 32:31"},"However concerning the ambassadors of the princes of Babylon, who sent to him to enquire of the wonder that was done in\nthe land, Allah left him, to try him, that he might know all that was in his heart.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"2CH 32:32"},"Now the rest of the acts of Hezekiah, and his good deeds, behold, they are written in the vision of Isaiah the prophet\nthe son of Amoz, in the book of the kings of Judah and Israel. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"2CH 32:33"},"Hezekiah slept with his fathers, and they buried him in the ascent of the tombs of the sons of Dawood. All Judah and the\ninhabitants of Jerusalem honoured him at his death. Manasseh his son reigned in his place.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"33","sid":"2CH 33"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 33:1"},"Manasseh was twelve years old when he began to reign, and he reigned fifty-five years in Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 33:2"},"He did that which was evil in the LORD’s sight, after the abominations of the nations whom the LORD cast out before the\nchildren of Israel. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 33:3"},"For he built again the high places which Hezekiah his father had broken down; and he raised up altars for the Baals, made\nAsheroth, and worshipped all the army of the sky, and served them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 33:4"},"He built altars in the LORD’s house, of which the LORD said, “My name shall be in Jerusalem forever.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 33:5"},"He built altars for all the army of the sky in the two courts of the LORD’s house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 33:6"},"He also made his children to pass through the fire in the valley of the son of Hinnom. He practised sorcery, divination,\nand witchcraft, and dealt with those who had familiar spirits and with wizards. He did much evil in the LORD’s sight, to\nprovoke him to anger. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 33:7"},"He set the engraved image of the idol, which he had made, in Allah’s house, of which Allah said to Dawood and to Sulaiman\nhis son, “In this house, and in Jerusalem, which I have chosen out of all the tribes of Israel, I will put my name forever.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 33:8"},"I will not any more remove the foot of Israel from off the land which I have appointed for your fathers, if only they will\nobserve to do all that I have commanded them, even all the law, the statutes, and the ordinances given by Musa.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 33:9"},"Manasseh seduced Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem, so that they did more evil than did the nations whom the LORD\ndestroyed before the children of Israel. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 33:10"},"The LORD spoke to Manasseh, and to his people; but they didn’t listen.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 33:11"},"Therefore the LORD brought on them the captains of the army of the king of Assyria, who took Manasseh in chains, bound\nhim with fetters, and carried him to Babylon. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 33:12"},"When he was in distress, he begged the LORD his Allah, and humbled himself greatly before Allah of his fathers.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 33:13"},"He prayed to him; and he was entreated by him, and heard his supplication, and brought him again to Jerusalem into his\nkingdom. Then Manasseh knew that the LORD was Allah. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 33:14"},"Now after this, he built an outer wall to Dawood’s city, on the west side of Gihon, in the valley, even to the entrance\nat the fish gate. He encircled Ophel with it, and raised it up to a very great height; and he put valiant captains in all the\nfortified cities of Judah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 33:15"},"He took away the foreign gods, and the idol out of the LORD’s house, and all the altars that he had built in the mountain\nof the LORD’s house, and in Jerusalem, and cast them out of the city.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 33:16"},"He built up the LORD’s altar, and offered sacrifices of peace offerings and of thanksgiving on it, and commanded Judah to\nserve the LORD, Allah of Israel. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CH 33:17"},"Nevertheless the people sacrificed still in the high places, but only to the LORD their Allah.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CH 33:18"},"Now the rest of the acts of Manasseh, and his prayer to his Allah, and the words of the seers who spoke to him in the\nname of the LORD, Allah of Israel, behold, they are written amongst the acts of the kings of Israel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CH 33:19"},"His prayer also, and how Allah was entreated of him, and all his sin and his trespass, and the places in which he built\nhigh places, and set up the Asherah poles and the engraved images, before he humbled himself: behold, they are written in the\nhistory of Hozai.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["33:19 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, the seers"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2CH 33:20"},"So Manasseh slept with his fathers, and they buried him in his own house; and Amon his son reigned in his place.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2CH 33:21"},"Amon was twenty-two years old when he began to reign; and he reigned two years in Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"2CH 33:22"},"He did that which was evil in the LORD’s sight, as did Manasseh his father; and Amon sacrificed to all the engraved\nimages which Manasseh his father had made, and served them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"2CH 33:23"},"He didn’t humble himself before the LORD, as Manasseh his father had humbled himself; but this same Amon trespassed more\nand more. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"2CH 33:24"},"His servants conspired against him, and put him to death in his own house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"2CH 33:25"},"But the people of the land killed all those who had conspired against king Amon; and the people of the land made Josiah\nhis son king in his place. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"34","sid":"2CH 34"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 34:1"},"Josiah was eight years old when he began to reign, and he reigned thirty-one years in Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 34:2"},"He did that which was right in the LORD’s eyes, and walked in the ways of Dawood his father, and didn’t turn away to the\nright hand or to the left. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 34:3"},"For in the eighth year of his reign, while he was yet young, he began to seek after Allah of Dawood his father; and in the\ntwelfth year he began to purge Judah and Jerusalem from the high places, the Asherah poles, the engraved images, and the molten\nimages. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 34:4"},"They broke down the altars of the Baals in his presence; and he cut down the incense altars that were on high above them.\nHe broke the Asherah poles, the engraved images, and the molten images in pieces, made dust of them, and scattered it on the\ngraves of those who had sacrificed to them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 34:5"},"He burnt the bones of the priests on their altars, and purged Judah and Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 34:6"},"He did this in the cities of Manasseh, Ephraim, and Simeon, even to Naphtali, around in their ruins.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 34:7"},"He broke down the altars, and beat the Asherah poles and the engraved images into powder, and cut down all the incense\naltars throughout all the land of Israel, then returned to Jerusalem.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 34:8"},"Now in the eighteenth year of his reign, when he had purged the land and the house, he sent Shaphan the son of Azaliah,\nand Maaseiah the governor of the city, and Joah the son of Joahaz the recorder, to repair the LORD his Allah’s house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 34:9"},"They came to Hilkiah the high priest, and delivered the money that was brought into Allah’s house, which the Levites, the\nkeepers of the threshold, had gathered from the hands of Manasseh, Ephraim, of all the remnant of Israel, of all Judah and\nBenjamin, and of the inhabitants of Jerusalem. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 34:10"},"They delivered it into the hands of the workmen who had the oversight of the LORD’s house; and the workmen who laboured\nin the LORD’s house gave it to mend and repair the house. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 34:11"},"They gave it to the carpenters and to the builders, to buy cut stone and timber for couplings, and to make beams for the\nhouses which the kings of Judah had destroyed. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 34:12"},"The men did the work faithfully. Their overseers were Jahath and Obadiah, the Levites, of the sons of Merari; and\nZakariya and Meshullam, of the sons of the Kohathites, to give direction; and others of the Levites, who were all skilful with\nmusical instruments. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 34:13"},"Also they were over the bearers of burdens, and directed all who did the work in every kind of service. Of the Levites,\nthere were scribes, officials, and gatekeepers. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 34:14"},"When they brought out the money that was brought into the LORD’s house, Hilkiah the priest found the book of the LORD’s\nlaw given by Musa. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 34:15"},"Hilkiah answered Shaphan the scribe, “I have found the book of the law in the LORD’s house.” So Hilkiah delivered the\nbook to Shaphan. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 34:16"},"Shaphan carried the book to the king, and moreover brought back word to the king, saying, “All that was committed to your\nservants, they are doing. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CH 34:17"},"They have emptied out the money that was found in the LORD’s house, and have delivered it into the hand of the overseers,\nand into the hand of the workmen.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CH 34:18"},"Shaphan the scribe told the king, saying, “Hilkiah the priest has delivered me a book.” Shaphan read from it to the king.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CH 34:19"},"When the king had heard the words of the law, he tore his clothes.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2CH 34:20"},"The king commanded Hilkiah, Ahikam the son of Shaphan, Abdon the son of Micah, Shaphan the scribe, and Asaiah the king’s\nservant, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2CH 34:21"},"“Go enquire of the LORD for me, and for those who are left in Israel and in Judah, concerning the words of the book that\nis found; for great is the LORD’s wrath that is poured out on us, because our fathers have not kept the LORD’s word, to do\naccording to all that is written in this book.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"2CH 34:22"},"So Hilkiah, and they whom the king had commanded, went to Huldah the prophetess, the wife of Shallum the son of Tokhath,\nthe son of Hasrah, keeper of the wardrobe (now she lived in Jerusalem in the second quarter), and they spoke to her to that\neffect. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"2CH 34:23"},"She said to them, “The LORD, Allah of Israel says: ‘Tell the man who sent you to me,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"2CH 34:24"},"“The LORD says, ‘Behold, I will bring evil on this place, and on its inhabitants, even all the curses that are written in\nthe book which they have read before the king of Judah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"2CH 34:25"},"Because they have forsaken me, and have burnt incense to other gods, that they might provoke me to anger with all the\nworks of their hands; therefore my wrath is poured out on this place, and it will not be quenched.’”’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"2CH 34:26"},"But to the king of Judah, who sent you to enquire of the LORD, you shall tell him this, ‘The LORD, Allah of Israel says:\n“About the words which you have heard, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"2CH 34:27"},"because your heart was tender, and you humbled yourself before Allah, when you heard his words against this place, and\nagainst its inhabitants, and have humbled yourself before me, and have torn your clothes, and wept before me, I also have heard\nyou,” says the LORD. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"2CH 34:28"},"“Behold, I will gather you to your fathers, and you will be gathered to your grave in peace. Your eyes won’t see all the\nevil that I will bring on this place and on its inhabitants.”’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They brought back word to the king. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"2CH 34:29"},"Then the king sent and gathered together all the elders of Judah and Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"2CH 34:30"},"The king went up to the LORD’s house, with all the men of Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem, the priests, the\nLevites, and all the people, both great and small; and he read in their hearing all the words of the book of the covenant that\nwas found in the LORD’s house. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"2CH 34:31"},"The king stood in his place, and made a covenant before the LORD, to walk after the LORD, and to keep his commandments,\nand his testimonies, and his statutes, with all his heart, and with all his soul, to perform the words of the covenant that\nwere written in this book. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"2CH 34:32"},"He caused all who were found in Jerusalem and Benjamin to stand. The inhabitants of Jerusalem did according to the\ncovenant of Allah, Allah of their fathers. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"2CH 34:33"},"Josiah took away all the abominations out of all the countries that belonged to the children of Israel, and made all who\nwere found in Israel to serve, even to serve the LORD their Allah. All his days they didn’t depart from following the LORD,\nAllah of their fathers. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"35","sid":"2CH 35"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 35:1"},"Josiah kept a Passover to the LORD in Jerusalem. They killed the Passover on the fourteenth day of the first month.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 35:2"},"He set the priests in their offices, and encouraged them in the service of the LORD’s house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 35:3"},"He said to the Levites who taught all Israel, who were holy to the LORD, “Put the holy ark in the house which Sulaiman the\nson of Dawood king of Israel built. It will no longer be a burden on your shoulders. Now serve Allah your LORD, and his people\nIsrael. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 35:4"},"Prepare yourselves after your fathers’ houses by your divisions, according to the writing of Dawood king of Israel, and\naccording to the writing of Sulaiman his son. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 35:5"},"Stand in the holy place according to the divisions of the fathers’ houses of your brothers the children of the people, and\nlet there be for each a portion of a fathers’ house of the Levites.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 35:6"},"Kill the Passover, sanctify yourselves, and prepare for your brothers, to do according to the LORD’s word by Musa.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 35:7"},"Josiah gave to the children of the people, of the flock, lambs and young goats, all of them for the Passover offerings, to\nall who were present, to the number of thirty thousand, and three thousand bulls. These were of the king’s substance.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 35:8"},"His princes gave for a free will offering to the people, to the priests, and to the Levites. Hilkiah, Zakariya, and\nJehiel, the rulers of Allah’s house, gave to the priests for the Passover offerings two thousand and six hundred small\nlivestock, and three hundred head of cattle. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 35:9"},"Conaniah also, and Shemaiah and Nethanel, his brothers, and Hashabiah, Jeiel, and Jozabad, the chiefs of the Levites, gave\nto the Levites for the Passover offerings five thousand small livestock and five hundred head of cattle.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 35:10"},"So the service was prepared, and the priests stood in their place, and the Levites by their divisions, according to the\nking’s commandment. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 35:11"},"They killed the Passover, and the priests sprinkled the blood which they received of their hand, and the Levites skinned\nthem. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 35:12"},"They removed the burnt offerings, that they might give them according to the divisions of the fathers’ houses of the\nchildren of the people, to offer to the LORD, as it is written in the book of Musa. They did the same with the cattle.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 35:13"},"They roasted the Passover with fire according to the ordinance. They boiled the holy offerings in pots, in cauldrons, and\nin pans, and carried them quickly to all the children of the people.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 35:14"},"Afterward they prepared for themselves and for the priests, because the priests the sons of Harun were busy with offering\nthe burnt offerings and the fat until night. Therefore the Levites prepared for themselves and for the priests the sons of\nHarun. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 35:15"},"The singers the sons of Asaph were in their place, according to the commandment of Dawood, Asaph, Heman, and Jeduthun the\nking’s seer; and the gatekeepers were at every gate. They didn’t need to depart from their service, because their brothers the\nLevites prepared for them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 35:16"},"So all the service of the LORD was prepared the same day, to keep the Passover, and to offer burnt offerings on the\nLORD’s altar, according to the commandment of king Josiah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CH 35:17"},"The children of Israel who were present kept the Passover at that time, and the feast of unleavened bread seven days.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CH 35:18"},"There was no Passover like that kept in Israel from the days of Samuel the prophet, nor did any of the kings of Israel\nkeep such a Passover as Josiah kept, with the priests, the Levites, and all Judah and Israel who were present, and the\ninhabitants of Jerusalem. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CH 35:19"},"This Passover was kept in the eighteenth year of the reign of Josiah.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2CH 35:20"},"After all this, when Josiah had prepared the temple, Neco king of Egypt went up to fight against Carchemish by the\nEuphrates, and Josiah went out against him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2CH 35:21"},"But he sent ambassadors to him, saying, “What have I to do with you, you king of Judah? I come not against you today, but\nagainst the house with which I have war. Allah has commanded me to make haste. Beware that it is Allah who is with me, that he\nnot destroy you.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"2CH 35:22"},"Nevertheless Josiah would not turn his face from him, but disguised himself, that he might fight with him, and didn’t\nlisten to the words of Neco from the mouth of Allah, and came to fight in the valley of Megiddo.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"2CH 35:23"},"The archers shot at king Josiah; and the king said to his servants, “Take me away, because I am seriously wounded!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"2CH 35:24"},"So his servants took him out of the chariot, and put him in the second chariot that he had, and brought him to Jerusalem;\nand he died, and was buried in the tombs of his fathers. All Judah and Jerusalem mourned for Josiah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"2CH 35:25"},"Jeremiah lamented for Josiah, and all the singing men and singing women spoke of Josiah in their lamentations to this\nday; and they made them an ordinance in Israel. Behold, they are written in the lamentations.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"2CH 35:26"},"Now the rest of the acts of Josiah, and his good deeds, according to that which is written in the LORD’s law,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"2CH 35:27"},"and his acts, first and last, behold, they are written in the book of the kings of Israel and Judah.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"36","sid":"2CH 36"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CH 36:1"},"Then the people of the land took Jehoahaz the son of Josiah, and made him king in his father’s place in Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CH 36:2"},"Joahaz was twenty-three years old when he began to reign; and he reigned three months in Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CH 36:3"},"The king of Egypt removed him from office at Jerusalem, and fined the land one hundred talents of silver and a\ntalent",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["36:3 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A talent is about 30 kilograms or 66 pounds or 965 Troy\nounces"]}],"caller":"+"}," of gold. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CH 36:4"},"The king of Egypt made Eliakim his brother king over Judah and Jerusalem, and changed his name to Jehoiakim. Neco took\nJoahaz his brother, and carried him to Egypt. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CH 36:5"},"Jehoiakim was twenty-five years old when he began to reign, and he reigned eleven years in Jerusalem. He did that which\nwas evil in the LORD his Allah’s sight. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CH 36:6"},"Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came up against him, and bound him in fetters to carry him to Babylon.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CH 36:7"},"Nebuchadnezzar also carried some of the vessels of the LORD’s house to Babylon, and put them in his temple at Babylon.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CH 36:8"},"Now the rest of the acts of Jehoiakim, and his abominations which he did, and that which was found in him, behold, they\nare written in the book of the kings of Israel and Judah; and Jehoiachin his son reigned in his place.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CH 36:9"},"Jehoiachin was eight years old when he began to reign, and he reigned three months and ten days in Jerusalem. He did that\nwhich was evil in the LORD’s sight. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CH 36:10"},"At the return of the year, king Nebuchadnezzar sent and brought him to Babylon, with the valuable vessels of the LORD’s\nhouse, and made Zedekiah his brother king over Judah and Jerusalem.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CH 36:11"},"Zedekiah was twenty-one years old when he began to reign, and he reigned eleven years in Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CH 36:12"},"He did that which was evil in the LORD his Allah’s sight. He didn’t humble himself before Jeremiah the prophet speaking\nfrom the LORD’s mouth. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CH 36:13"},"He also rebelled against king Nebuchadnezzar, who had made him swear by Allah; but he stiffened his neck, and hardened\nhis heart against turning to the LORD, Allah of Israel. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CH 36:14"},"Moreover all the chiefs of the priests, and the people, trespassed very greatly after all the abominations of the\nnations; and they polluted the LORD’s house which he had made holy in Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CH 36:15"},"The LORD, Allah of their fathers, sent to them by his messengers, rising up early and sending, because he had compassion\non his people, and on his dwelling place; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CH 36:16"},"but they mocked the messengers of Allah, and despised his words, and scoffed at his prophets, until the LORD’s wrath\narose against his people, until there was no remedy. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CH 36:17"},"Therefore he brought on them the king of the Chaldeans, who killed their young men with the sword in the house of their\nsanctuary, and had no compassion on young man or virgin, old man or grey-headed. He gave them all into his hand.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CH 36:18"},"All the vessels of Allah’s house, great and small, and the treasures of the LORD’s house, and the treasures of the king,\nand of his princes, all these he brought to Babylon. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CH 36:19"},"They burnt Allah’s house, and broke down the wall of Jerusalem, and burnt all its palaces with fire, and destroyed all of\nits valuable vessels. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2CH 36:20"},"He carried those who had escaped from the sword away to Babylon, and they were servants to him and his sons until the\nreign of the kingdom of Persia, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2CH 36:21"},"to fulfil the LORD’s word by Jeremiah’s mouth, until the land had enjoyed its Sabbaths. As long as it lay desolate, it\nkept Sabbath, to fulfil seventy years. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"2CH 36:22"},"Now in the first year of Dhul-Qarnayn king of Persia, that the LORD’s word by the mouth of Jeremiah might be\naccomplished, the LORD stirred up the spirit of Dhul-Qarnayn king of Persia, so that he made a proclamation throughout all his\nkingdom, and put it also in writing, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"2CH 36:23"},"“Dhul-Qarnayn king of Persia says, ‘The LORD, Allah of heaven, has given all the kingdoms of the earth to me; and he has\ncommanded me to build him a house in Jerusalem, which is in Judah. Whoever there is amongst you of all his people, the LORD his\nAllah be with him, and let him go up.’” "]}]}